WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.643 --> 00:00:17.133
Dr. Greene?

2
00:00:18.412 --> 00:00:19.845
Dr. Greene!

3
00:00:21.950 --> 00:00:23.042
What is it?

4
00:00:23.252 --> 00:00:24.514
Patient for you. Dr. Greene.

5
00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:26.646
Can't the intern take it?

6
00:00:26.855 --> 00:00:28.253
No. it's for you.

7
00:00:28.456 --> 00:00:30.822
- What time is it?
- Five o'clock.

8
00:00:35.664 --> 00:00:37.291
All right.

9
00:00:39.635 --> 00:00:42.035
- Can't the intern take it?
- It's Dr. Ross.

10
00:00:45.374 --> 00:00:47.274
Dr. Ross.

11
00:00:47.542 --> 00:00:48.839
I'll be right there.

12
00:01:27.617 --> 00:01:28.949
Come on. Doug.

13
00:01:29.786 --> 00:01:32.085
Markie-boy! Did I wake you up?

14
00:01:32.289 --> 00:01:33.688
Yes. you did.

15
00:01:34.191 --> 00:01:36.352
I want you to know
you're a real friend

16
00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:38.494
- That's all right.
- Real friend.

17
00:01:38.696 --> 00:01:40.823
- Do we have a room?
- Room 3 is free.

18
00:01:41.031 --> 00:01:42.795
Room three is free!

19
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.195
Three is free. Free for three.

20
00:01:45.469 --> 00:01:47.461
- Come on. Doug.
- All right. I gotcha.

21
00:01:47.671 --> 00:01:49.606
<i>But come ye back</i>

22
00:01:49.808 --> 00:01:52.605
<i>When summer's in the meadow</i>

23
00:01:57.716 --> 00:01:59.013
I can't tell you...

24
00:01:59.217 --> 00:02:01.742
...how much I appreciate this. Mark.

25
00:02:02.454 --> 00:02:04.150
I'm a little under the weather.

26
00:02:12.164 --> 00:02:15.257
D5. NS. I need the dextrose.

27
00:02:15.468 --> 00:02:18.459
- Give him 600 of ASA.
- Aspirin.

28
00:02:18.636 --> 00:02:20.036
I almost forgot aspirin.

29
00:02:20.506 --> 00:02:22.132
So anyway...

30
00:02:23.976 --> 00:02:25.944
...she says to me. she says...

31
00:02:26.745 --> 00:02:30.705
..."I didn't know that pediatricians
could be so sexy."

32
00:02:30.916 --> 00:02:34.853
And I said. "Honey. you ain't seen
nothing yet."

33
00:02:37.456 --> 00:02:40.254
All right. Give me the fast drip.
I need the hydration.

34
00:02:40.460 --> 00:02:42.894
Don't worry. Doug. Just lie back.

35
00:02:45.432 --> 00:02:47.160
How's your beautiful wife. Jennifer?

36
00:02:47.367 --> 00:02:48.561
She's fine. really.

37
00:02:48.769 --> 00:02:50.599
You two settle your problems?

38
00:02:50.804 --> 00:02:52.169
Everything's okay.

39
00:02:52.372 --> 00:02:54.772
Hate to lose you in the ER. you know.

40
00:02:55.609 --> 00:02:57.736
- Lie back.
- I am.

41
00:03:00.547 --> 00:03:03.015
I can't tell you how much
I appreciate this.

42
00:03:03.217 --> 00:03:04.774
Really do.

43
00:03:05.919 --> 00:03:07.386
Here's your aspirin.

44
00:03:07.587 --> 00:03:09.351
Give him 2000cc's
in a fast drip.

45
00:03:09.556 --> 00:03:11.081
Don't let it run dry.

46
00:03:11.292 --> 00:03:12.623
Does he always do this?

47
00:03:12.827 --> 00:03:14.818
Only on his nights off.

48
00:03:15.863 --> 00:03:18.730
I'm going to bed.
Wake me at 6:30.

49
00:03:30.845 --> 00:03:32.039
Doctor Greene?

50
00:03:32.246 --> 00:03:34.112
Doctor Greene? Mark!

51
00:03:35.017 --> 00:03:36.245
What is it?

52
00:03:36.452 --> 00:03:38.886
Can I give Mrs. Williston
more Demerol?

53
00:03:39.087 --> 00:03:40.817
50 milligrams. I.M.

54
00:03:41.056 --> 00:03:42.182
Thanks. Mark.

55
00:03:48.997 --> 00:03:50.464
- Dr. Greene!
- What is it?

56
00:03:50.666 --> 00:03:52.600
6:30. Dr. Greene.

57
00:03:59.976 --> 00:04:01.341
- Hey. Timmy.
- Morning. Dr. Lewis.

58
00:04:01.544 --> 00:04:03.238
Oh. Dr. Lewis!

59
00:04:05.514 --> 00:04:07.107
Thank you.

60
00:04:08.184 --> 00:04:10.448
- Good morning. Dr. Benton.
- Hey. Jerry.

61
00:04:11.554 --> 00:04:14.148
<i>This was the scene at 6: 15
this morning...</i>

62
00:04:14.357 --> 00:04:17.155
<i>... where a building
collapsed during construction.</i>

63
00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:19.226
Any estimate on the injuries?

64
00:04:20.464 --> 00:04:21.930
How long before they arrive?

65
00:04:22.132 --> 00:04:25.000
<i>- 12 people injured
and 2 dead.</i>

66
00:04:25.702 --> 00:04:28.570
Oh. yeah? That soon?

67
00:04:29.038 --> 00:04:30.734
- What's up. Timmy?
- Hey. Dr. Benton.

68
00:04:30.941 --> 00:04:33.273
Notify trauma.
An accident in the Loop.

69
00:04:33.477 --> 00:04:35.672
Twelve injuries. seven critical.

70
00:04:38.449 --> 00:04:40.679
Good day for us surgeons.

71
00:04:40.885 --> 00:04:42.409
Mrs. Willis in 4 needs a CBC.

72
00:04:42.620 --> 00:04:46.886
The man in 5 is a rule-out MI waiting
for cardiac enzymes and 12 units.

73
00:04:47.091 --> 00:04:50.822
Dr. Ross is in 3. sleeping it off.
Wake him and get him out of there.

74
00:04:51.029 --> 00:04:52.155
I need a uric acid...

75
00:04:52.364 --> 00:04:53.524
What's this is all about?

76
00:04:53.732 --> 00:04:55.962
Building collapsed.
They're sending us a dozen.

77
00:04:56.167 --> 00:04:58.658
- Yeah. well. who's on?
- Just us.

78
00:04:58.869 --> 00:05:02.328
Forget all that. Call Susan Lewis.
Call the 7th and 8th floor.

79
00:05:02.541 --> 00:05:05.533
Tell them we need anybody
they can spare. Do that now.

80
00:05:09.514 --> 00:05:10.879
Take him to Trauma Room 2.

81
00:05:11.082 --> 00:05:13.847
What's your name. sir?
Can you tell me your name?

82
00:05:14.052 --> 00:05:16.214
- Next to 3. That way.
- Which way?

83
00:05:16.388 --> 00:05:17.378
That way!

84
00:05:21.459 --> 00:05:24.293
Take him to 1.
Down to the end. on the right.

85
00:05:24.497 --> 00:05:26.897
- What's your name. sir?
- It's Wilson.

86
00:05:27.098 --> 00:05:28.657
What is your address?

87
00:05:31.737 --> 00:05:32.965
Mr. Wilson?

88
00:05:33.172 --> 00:05:34.537
Get it later.

89
00:05:34.740 --> 00:05:36.935
Let's go. Let's bring him in.

90
00:05:38.511 --> 00:05:41.208
And on my count. On three.
One. two...

91
00:05:41.414 --> 00:05:42.404
...three!

92
00:05:44.250 --> 00:05:45.308
How you doing. sir?

93
00:05:45.519 --> 00:05:47.645
Don't worry.
Everything will be fine.

94
00:05:47.854 --> 00:05:50.879
Sorry about the suit.
So is it just your hand?

95
00:05:51.090 --> 00:05:52.148
Let's see. Light?

96
00:05:52.359 --> 00:05:53.656
Light! Let's move.

97
00:05:53.860 --> 00:05:56.090
Have nice. pleasant thoughts.

98
00:05:56.296 --> 00:05:58.230
Let's have a CBC...

99
00:05:58.432 --> 00:06:01.458
...type and cross-match.
We got a pre- op here.

100
00:06:01.668 --> 00:06:04.068
Notify the O.R.. get us a room.

101
00:06:04.271 --> 00:06:07.934
Call Vascular and call Orthopedic.
Tell them to come down now.

102
00:06:08.142 --> 00:06:09.904
This is their lucky day.

103
00:06:10.110 --> 00:06:14.207
Mr. Wilson. your hand is barely
attached. but it's gonna be okay.

104
00:06:14.415 --> 00:06:16.848
Give me an EKG and X-ray
of his wrist and hand.

105
00:06:17.050 --> 00:06:19.815
- Can you feel anything in your hand?
- No.

106
00:06:20.387 --> 00:06:22.185
We'll save your hand.
don't worry.

107
00:06:22.390 --> 00:06:23.652
Clear!

108
00:06:25.125 --> 00:06:27.026
Mr. Jackson. where does it hurt?

109
00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:29.692
Where does it hurt. Mr. Jackson?

110
00:06:29.897 --> 00:06:32.059
Does it hurt when you breathe in?

111
00:06:32.667 --> 00:06:34.658
Have you been coughing up any blood?

112
00:06:34.869 --> 00:06:36.861
Okay. let me take a listen.

113
00:06:39.241 --> 00:06:40.265
Dr. Lewis!

114
00:06:40.476 --> 00:06:42.444
Okay. Where are we taking him?

115
00:06:50.486 --> 00:06:53.046
Do you have any pain in your head?

116
00:06:53.255 --> 00:06:55.120
How about your neck?
Any pain here?

117
00:06:57.893 --> 00:07:00.088
What I want you to do now...

118
00:07:00.296 --> 00:07:03.629
I want you to tell me if
it hurts you when you breathe.

119
00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:05.160
I don't get a BP.

120
00:07:05.368 --> 00:07:07.927
Start two large bore IVs.
Saline. wide open.

121
00:07:08.137 --> 00:07:11.733
Type and cross for 10 units. get me
4 units of O-negative. stat.

122
00:07:11.941 --> 00:07:15.206
Drop an NG tube
and get Dr. Benton in here.

123
00:07:15.412 --> 00:07:17.403
This is no place for a pediatrician.

124
00:07:17.614 --> 00:07:19.844
No sensation: Radial. median or ulnar.

125
00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:22.382
No pulses. Color and
temperature as you see.

126
00:07:22.585 --> 00:07:24.644
He's gotten 500cc's saline.

127
00:07:24.854 --> 00:07:26.845
Crit's 32-5. type and cross-match sent.

128
00:07:27.057 --> 00:07:29.821
X-ray's waiting. O.R. Will have
a room in 10 minutes.

129
00:07:30.027 --> 00:07:31.494
Let's get him out of here.

130
00:07:31.761 --> 00:07:33.956
You think you can save the hand?

131
00:07:34.164 --> 00:07:35.461
It looks good. I think so.

132
00:07:35.666 --> 00:07:38.191
I told him you could.
He's counting on you.

133
00:07:38.402 --> 00:07:39.868
Peter. you're a smart-ass.

134
00:07:40.070 --> 00:07:42.539
You'd love to do this case.
wouldn't you?

135
00:07:43.674 --> 00:07:45.335
I'm ready.
I could do it.

136
00:07:45.543 --> 00:07:46.805
You're a resident. Peter.

137
00:07:47.011 --> 00:07:49.445
You're years from a case like this.

138
00:07:51.782 --> 00:07:53.249
- How many fingers?
- Three.

139
00:07:53.451 --> 00:07:55.544
- What's your name?
- Jeff Barr.

140
00:07:55.753 --> 00:07:57.653
- Where are you?
- Cook County General.

141
00:07:57.855 --> 00:07:59.824
- What's today?
- St. Patrick's Day.

142
00:08:00.024 --> 00:08:02.686
You're fine.
Get a set of facial bones.

143
00:08:02.894 --> 00:08:05.260
You're gonna be just fine. Mr. Barr.

144
00:08:05.897 --> 00:08:07.797
- You're beautiful. doc.
- Thank you.

145
00:08:07.999 --> 00:08:09.590
- You married?
- No. I'm a doctor.

146
00:08:09.801 --> 00:08:11.826
- Then. listen...
- Take it easy. Mr. Barr.

147
00:08:12.037 --> 00:08:14.699
You don't want to fall on your face
twice in one day.

148
00:08:16.476 --> 00:08:17.773
How much did she vomit?

149
00:08:17.976 --> 00:08:19.341
A couple hundred cc's.

150
00:08:19.544 --> 00:08:21.705
Would you please take a deep breath?

151
00:08:21.913 --> 00:08:24.347
Good. Now another.
Any pain there?

152
00:08:25.217 --> 00:08:26.845
Okay. how about here?

153
00:08:28.187 --> 00:08:29.211
Call O.R.. get a room.

154
00:08:29.389 --> 00:08:30.855
- What is her crit?
- 23.

155
00:08:32.525 --> 00:08:33.856
Wait a minute. Here we go!

156
00:08:34.060 --> 00:08:35.459
No pulse. Code blue.

157
00:08:35.828 --> 00:08:37.796
- Call the time.
- 8:37.

158
00:08:38.464 --> 00:08:40.329
Paddles!
That's a shockable rhythm.

159
00:08:40.533 --> 00:08:42.559
Let's move! Here we go.

160
00:08:42.769 --> 00:08:44.031
Nice and easy.

161
00:08:44.437 --> 00:08:45.631
Clear!

162
00:08:49.275 --> 00:08:51.175
- No response.
- Get me an amp of epi...

163
00:08:51.377 --> 00:08:53.938
...and a hundred lidocaine.
Let's move it.

164
00:08:54.548 --> 00:08:58.006
Okay. what've we got here?
Where are the paramedics?

165
00:08:58.351 --> 00:08:59.683
Get his clothes off him.

166
00:08:59.887 --> 00:09:02.378
Give me something. I can't stand it!

167
00:09:02.589 --> 00:09:04.580
I'll give you something for the pain.

168
00:09:04.792 --> 00:09:07.523
Notify the orthopods we have
an open fracture.

169
00:09:07.761 --> 00:09:09.889
Give him tetanus and 5
of morphine right away.

170
00:09:10.097 --> 00:09:11.894
- Does it hurt anywhere else?
- My knee.

171
00:09:12.100 --> 00:09:13.691
- Need help?
- Check his knee.

172
00:09:16.069 --> 00:09:17.059
Here we go.

173
00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:22.840
We got patients on surgical
2 and 3. One of them looks bad.

174
00:09:23.043 --> 00:09:24.909
Fine. but this woman's
heart stopped...

175
00:09:25.113 --> 00:09:27.980
...and she needs it. Call the AR.
- They're in surgery.

176
00:09:28.183 --> 00:09:29.775
Get them.
Can't you see I'm busy?

177
00:09:29.984 --> 00:09:31.042
- Time?
- Two minutes.

178
00:09:31.252 --> 00:09:34.745
Come on. sweetheart.
You make us a little nervous here.

179
00:09:34.956 --> 00:09:36.150
Paddles. Let's go.

180
00:09:38.026 --> 00:09:39.084
Clear.

181
00:09:41.095 --> 00:09:42.255
Is that a blip?

182
00:09:43.531 --> 00:09:44.896
There it is.

183
00:09:45.733 --> 00:09:46.961
Come on.

184
00:09:47.168 --> 00:09:48.636
Come on back to us.

185
00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:51.898
Keep it pumping.
I think she's coming back.

186
00:09:52.107 --> 00:09:53.574
Bring her back for me. baby.

187
00:09:54.643 --> 00:09:58.010
Come on back to us.
Come on. baby. Yes!

188
00:09:58.214 --> 00:09:59.977
That one to Trauma 3.

189
00:10:00.182 --> 00:10:02.241
That's down the hall and to the left.

190
00:10:04.920 --> 00:10:06.114
Call Pathology. We got one...

191
00:10:06.322 --> 00:10:08.688
...who won't be charged.
The name's Canelli.

192
00:10:09.425 --> 00:10:11.950
Canelli?
Relatives of Robert Canelli.

193
00:10:12.161 --> 00:10:13.754
Right here.

194
00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:18.057
- I'm his son.
- Hi. I'm Mark Greene.

195
00:10:18.268 --> 00:10:19.428
My father. he's...

196
00:10:19.636 --> 00:10:22.628
Your father was in an accident.
you know that?

197
00:10:22.839 --> 00:10:23.828
Come with me. please.

198
00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:27.908
No. just tell me. He's here. right?
Just tell me.

199
00:10:28.678 --> 00:10:32.580
Mr. Canelli. your father
had a heart attack...

200
00:10:32.783 --> 00:10:36.344
...and we were unable to revive him.
I'm sorry.

201
00:10:37.888 --> 00:10:40.186
You bastard! You bastards!

202
00:10:43.628 --> 00:10:45.528
You're sorry?

203
00:10:59.143 --> 00:11:01.271
Come over here.

204
00:11:04.148 --> 00:11:05.376
That will make you
feel better.

205
00:11:05.584 --> 00:11:08.848
And we'll have you in the O.R.
In no time. okay?

206
00:11:12.591 --> 00:11:14.923
- Any others?
- No. that's it.

207
00:11:15.127 --> 00:11:17.925
- That's it?
- Yeah. Last two were DO A.

208
00:11:19.498 --> 00:11:20.624
That's it.

209
00:11:20.832 --> 00:11:22.561
Yeah. for now.

210
00:11:38.450 --> 00:11:41.352
<i>Orderly. please bring
a wheelchair to Admitting.</i>

211
00:11:41.554 --> 00:11:44.546
<i>Orderly. please bring
a wheelchair to Admitting.</i>

212
00:11:44.724 --> 00:11:46.749
- Where's Ross?
- He went to change.

213
00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:48.895
Somebody threw up on him.

214
00:11:49.095 --> 00:11:51.859
- That lady.
- The lady who arrested?

215
00:11:52.065 --> 00:11:53.896
- She make it?
- We got her going again.

216
00:11:54.435 --> 00:11:56.629
She's got a junctional rhythm.
but she's going.

217
00:11:56.837 --> 00:11:58.361
What about that guy's hand?

218
00:11:58.571 --> 00:12:00.301
They're still in surgery.

219
00:12:00.507 --> 00:12:03.304
They're gonna be working
all day on that one.

220
00:12:04.612 --> 00:12:06.045
- Anybody want coffee?
- I do.

221
00:12:06.547 --> 00:12:07.536
How do you take it?

222
00:12:07.748 --> 00:12:09.716
Same as yesterday and the day before.

223
00:12:09.917 --> 00:12:12.181
And they call me a smart-ass.

224
00:12:12.621 --> 00:12:14.053
You get any sleep last night?

225
00:12:14.254 --> 00:12:15.585
About an hour.

226
00:12:16.157 --> 00:12:19.125
The nurses raided the coffee.
Why don't they make their own?

227
00:12:19.326 --> 00:12:20.658
I'm gonna tell them.

228
00:12:20.862 --> 00:12:22.124
Never mind.

229
00:12:24.565 --> 00:12:27.056
Okay. Never mind.

230
00:12:29.571 --> 00:12:32.199
Aren't we getting
some new students today?

231
00:12:32.540 --> 00:12:34.235
Yeah. I think so.

232
00:12:34.442 --> 00:12:37.070
I hope they're good.
The last two were hopeless.

233
00:12:43.618 --> 00:12:46.553
- Something wrong?
- Oh. you bet there is.

234
00:12:46.756 --> 00:12:50.453
We're out of coffee again because
the nurses have been taking it.

235
00:12:51.026 --> 00:12:54.087
- Make some more.
- Make some more?

236
00:12:54.764 --> 00:12:57.198
We work 36 hours on. 18 off...

237
00:12:57.400 --> 00:12:59.527
...which is 90 hours a week.
52 weeks a year.

238
00:12:59.735 --> 00:13:03.933
For that we are paid
$23.739 before taxes.

239
00:13:04.140 --> 00:13:06.301
And we also have to make the coffee?

240
00:13:06.709 --> 00:13:07.767
My heart is breaking.

241
00:13:12.682 --> 00:13:15.015
- Where are the filters?
- In the refrigerator.

242
00:13:15.685 --> 00:13:19.143
<i>Dr. Greene. your wife is waiting
in the cafeteria. Dr. Greene.</i>

243
00:13:19.355 --> 00:13:20.948
Damn it!

244
00:13:24.661 --> 00:13:26.356
Everything's fine.

245
00:13:35.072 --> 00:13:36.937
Morning. Dr. Greene.

246
00:13:46.550 --> 00:13:48.018
Hey. Mom! Look!

247
00:13:48.219 --> 00:13:49.913
Two more bites. baby. Please?

248
00:13:50.120 --> 00:13:51.486
Then you're done.

249
00:13:53.024 --> 00:13:55.993
- Hi. Rachel.
- Hey. Dad. look!

250
00:13:56.427 --> 00:13:57.860
Oh. look!

251
00:13:58.062 --> 00:14:00.395
Grilled cheese sandwich
for breakfast.

252
00:14:01.499 --> 00:14:04.195
I gave in. What can I say?

253
00:14:04.402 --> 00:14:05.699
You're late.

254
00:14:05.903 --> 00:14:08.566
Sorry. we had a big one.
A building collapsed.

255
00:14:08.774 --> 00:14:10.833
Mommy's reading about tarts.

256
00:14:11.309 --> 00:14:12.833
Torts.

257
00:14:14.313 --> 00:14:15.610
Are you getting any sleep?

258
00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:17.337
Yeah. yeah. I'm okay.

259
00:14:19.017 --> 00:14:21.417
- You look tired.
- Yeah. Dad. You look tired.

260
00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:22.882
Oh. I do. do I?

261
00:14:23.956 --> 00:14:25.890
Are you gonna finish that?

262
00:14:26.091 --> 00:14:27.615
You mind if I eat it?

263
00:14:30.362 --> 00:14:32.853
Dr. Harris' office called
to confirm your meeting.

264
00:14:33.298 --> 00:14:36.097
Oh. jeez! That was today.

265
00:14:36.903 --> 00:14:38.029
You can still go. right?

266
00:14:38.371 --> 00:14:40.202
Yeah. yeah. I guess.

267
00:14:40.473 --> 00:14:42.407
You're not gonna forget
or get too busy?

268
00:14:42.976 --> 00:14:44.068
I'll go.

269
00:14:49.382 --> 00:14:50.781
What's so funny?

270
00:14:50.984 --> 00:14:53.214
- You know you're gonna hate it.
- Maybe not.

271
00:14:53.419 --> 00:14:55.649
At least the patients
don't throw up on you.

272
00:14:55.822 --> 00:14:56.811
Who threw up?

273
00:14:57.757 --> 00:14:58.883
Who threw up?

274
00:14:59.092 --> 00:15:00.583
Nobody threw up.

275
00:15:03.130 --> 00:15:06.327
It's just that between your hours
and my studying...

276
00:15:06.534 --> 00:15:08.934
...I feel like we never see
each other.

277
00:15:10.805 --> 00:15:13.171
I'll go meet Harris today. okay?

278
00:15:16.677 --> 00:15:18.406
I just hope you like it.

279
00:15:20.848 --> 00:15:21.906
Look at this.

280
00:15:25.954 --> 00:15:28.387
It's the first tailored
white coat I've seen.

281
00:15:28.589 --> 00:15:30.353
- Isn't he lovely?
- Lovely.

282
00:15:31.025 --> 00:15:32.755
Think he knows anything?

283
00:15:32.961 --> 00:15:34.552
He knows how to dress.

284
00:15:35.729 --> 00:15:38.961
He's my student. I'll find out.

285
00:15:41.036 --> 00:15:42.230
- John Carter?
- Yes. sir.

286
00:15:42.437 --> 00:15:43.768
Peter Benton.

287
00:15:43.972 --> 00:15:45.599
- You the surgical student?
- Third year.

288
00:15:45.807 --> 00:15:49.471
We'll spend a lot of time together.
so let me show you around.

289
00:15:49.679 --> 00:15:53.012
The Admitting desk is where you
page someone or get a chart.

290
00:15:53.216 --> 00:15:55.343
Don't shake his hand.
He's afraid of disease.

291
00:15:55.551 --> 00:15:58.212
In the lab we do crits.
counts. spin-downs.

292
00:15:58.420 --> 00:16:03.324
Mark chemistries "stat" whether
you want it fast or not.

293
00:16:03.526 --> 00:16:08.122
The chem lab is 7022. The heme lab
is 6944. Memorize it.

294
00:16:08.698 --> 00:16:09.960
IVs are given to everybody.

295
00:16:10.166 --> 00:16:11.633
Use an angiocath and 16 needle.

296
00:16:11.834 --> 00:16:14.360
You need a large bore
to transfuse them.

297
00:16:14.571 --> 00:16:17.095
- Can you start an IV?
- Actually. no.

298
00:16:17.273 --> 00:16:18.262
Aren't you third year?

299
00:16:18.441 --> 00:16:21.206
All I've done are
dermatology and psychiatry.

300
00:16:21.411 --> 00:16:23.241
The well-dressed specialties. huh?

301
00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:27.143
You'll find surgeons try to
help people. not just bill them.

302
00:16:27.351 --> 00:16:30.445
Pull the skin tight so the veins
don't roll. and go in low.

303
00:16:30.654 --> 00:16:32.484
Once in. pull this out
and hook it here.

304
00:16:32.689 --> 00:16:36.181
This is Carol Hathaway. the head nurse.
John Carter.

305
00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:37.349
Terrific. isn't she?

306
00:16:37.561 --> 00:16:40.531
She dates an orthopod who used
to be a Big Ten tackle.

307
00:16:42.132 --> 00:16:43.724
You want to tape it.

308
00:16:43.935 --> 00:16:46.732
Moderate flow. two or three
drips per second.

309
00:16:46.937 --> 00:16:49.805
That's it. That's all
there is to it.

310
00:16:56.014 --> 00:16:59.177
All along here you have
the medical examining rooms.

311
00:16:59.384 --> 00:17:01.852
It's where the pill-pushers
kill their victims.

312
00:17:02.053 --> 00:17:03.611
But this...

313
00:17:04.822 --> 00:17:07.017
...this is the surgical room.

314
00:17:07.358 --> 00:17:09.519
This is where the real action is.

315
00:17:11.829 --> 00:17:15.162
We use this phone to
call the O.R.. 6440.

316
00:17:15.366 --> 00:17:18.063
X-ray is around the corner.
They're idiots.

317
00:17:18.270 --> 00:17:19.861
They scare the patients.

318
00:17:20.071 --> 00:17:23.235
Whenever you can.
go with the patients to X-ray.

319
00:17:23.441 --> 00:17:26.411
Don't let them get scared.
Don't let them get hurt.

320
00:17:26.712 --> 00:17:29.146
Here's Dr. Morgenstern.
He's the head of ER.

321
00:17:29.348 --> 00:17:31.647
Watch out. he eats students for lunch.

322
00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:32.942
David Morgenstern.

323
00:17:33.152 --> 00:17:37.111
- When did that severed hand go up?
- A vascular took it up an hour ago.

324
00:17:37.324 --> 00:17:39.416
Dr. Benton is one of
our best residents.

325
00:17:39.626 --> 00:17:41.217
Learn everything you can from him.

326
00:17:41.895 --> 00:17:43.385
Except attitude.

327
00:17:44.130 --> 00:17:46.530
- He didn't mean that.
- Yes. he did!

328
00:17:47.399 --> 00:17:50.460
You'll sew people up here.
Do you know how to suture?

329
00:17:50.670 --> 00:17:53.002
Okay. I'll teach you.

330
00:17:53.206 --> 00:17:55.674
- Is there anyone to sew?
- How would I know?

331
00:17:55.875 --> 00:17:59.937
I love this great spirit of
camaraderie. Everyone wants to help.

332
00:18:00.147 --> 00:18:01.670
Here's the suture room.

333
00:18:03.283 --> 00:18:06.343
Good morning. I'm Dr. Benton.
This is Dr. Carter.

334
00:18:06.553 --> 00:18:08.181
Let's have a look.

335
00:18:09.623 --> 00:18:12.558
- How'd you do this?
- Broke one of the breakfast dishes.

336
00:18:12.760 --> 00:18:16.820
Don't worry. We'll have you
fixed up right away.

337
00:18:17.631 --> 00:18:19.997
- Now. can you feel this?
- Yes!

338
00:18:20.201 --> 00:18:22.795
- Can you move your finger?
- It's just a cut!

339
00:18:23.004 --> 00:18:26.269
We have a policeman coming in
with a gunshot wound.

340
00:18:26.474 --> 00:18:29.238
Put him in Room 2. notify X-ray.
I'll be right there.

341
00:18:29.444 --> 00:18:31.343
Now. here's all your stuff.

342
00:18:31.579 --> 00:18:34.481
Ask if she's allergic
to locals or any drugs.

343
00:18:34.682 --> 00:18:38.619
This is lidocaine. but call it
Novocaine. They've heard of that.

344
00:18:39.453 --> 00:18:40.784
Any allergy to Novocaine?

345
00:18:40.989 --> 00:18:42.183
My teeth are okay.

346
00:18:42.391 --> 00:18:45.952
- No reactions. rashes. anything?
- No. of course not.

347
00:18:46.161 --> 00:18:48.629
You inject both sides of the wound.

348
00:18:48.830 --> 00:18:52.789
You have to put on surgical gloves.
You know how to do that?

349
00:18:54.470 --> 00:18:56.700
Great. Here we go.

350
00:19:00.243 --> 00:19:01.574
Here you go. Dr. Ross.

351
00:19:01.778 --> 00:19:03.244
Thank you. Nance.

352
00:19:04.346 --> 00:19:05.336
Dr. Ross.

353
00:19:05.848 --> 00:19:08.146
Tracy Young.
I'm your third- year student.

354
00:19:08.351 --> 00:19:10.319
Hello. Tracy Young.
Nice to meet you.

355
00:19:10.520 --> 00:19:13.045
We'll be working
very closely together...

356
00:19:13.256 --> 00:19:16.089
Not that closely. but
I'll do my best to help you.

357
00:19:16.292 --> 00:19:19.056
- I'd like to get started.
- Just being friendly.

358
00:19:19.729 --> 00:19:22.027
I've got all the friends
I need. thanks.

359
00:19:22.231 --> 00:19:23.357
Shall we get started?

360
00:19:29.372 --> 00:19:31.000
Evert the edges and space them...

361
00:19:31.208 --> 00:19:33.403
...because the tissues will be swelling.

362
00:19:33.610 --> 00:19:34.941
Space them this way.

363
00:19:35.144 --> 00:19:36.476
The policeman's here.

364
00:19:36.680 --> 00:19:39.649
Okay. I'm coming. Here. you finish.

365
00:19:50.928 --> 00:19:53.362
Okay. this isn't going to hurt at all.

366
00:19:58.336 --> 00:19:59.928
Now. what happened. Billy?

367
00:20:00.137 --> 00:20:02.902
The school sent him home.
They said he vomited blood.

368
00:20:04.209 --> 00:20:05.699
Can you tell me what happened?

369
00:20:05.909 --> 00:20:09.744
He's a very high-strung child.
Always very tense. very nervous.

370
00:20:09.948 --> 00:20:12.884
Maybe you better wait outside
while I examine your son.

371
00:20:13.051 --> 00:20:14.041
It's procedure.

372
00:20:14.219 --> 00:20:17.052
I should be here!
I'm worried about Billy. He needs me.

373
00:20:17.255 --> 00:20:18.655
Please wait outside.

374
00:20:18.858 --> 00:20:21.417
Look. doctor. this is my son...

375
00:20:21.626 --> 00:20:24.357
...and I want to be here.
He's very high- strung!

376
00:20:24.563 --> 00:20:26.827
You're absolutely right.
You love your son.

377
00:20:27.099 --> 00:20:28.999
You want him treated immediately.

378
00:20:29.667 --> 00:20:31.533
So it's best...

379
00:20:31.871 --> 00:20:35.898
...if you have a seat outside here.
And we'll be right with you.

380
00:20:44.651 --> 00:20:47.585
Hey. kiddo. All right.

381
00:20:47.820 --> 00:20:48.844
Did you vomit blood?

382
00:20:50.824 --> 00:20:52.415
Do you have any pain?

383
00:20:53.093 --> 00:20:55.152
Okay. can you point to the pain?

384
00:20:57.097 --> 00:20:58.291
Right in here.

385
00:20:58.899 --> 00:21:00.924
Have you vomited blood before?

386
00:21:01.134 --> 00:21:02.294
Many times?

387
00:21:10.711 --> 00:21:13.838
First eight-year-old
ulcer patient I've seen.

388
00:21:18.552 --> 00:21:21.044
You still here?
You doing a Sistine Chapel?

389
00:21:21.255 --> 00:21:24.713
Finish her up. start an IV
in Room 2. Bye. ma'am.

390
00:21:25.193 --> 00:21:27.024
Nurse. could you bandage this?

391
00:21:27.929 --> 00:21:30.557
- Thank you. doctor.
- You're very welcome.

392
00:21:30.765 --> 00:21:32.233
When do I get my stitches out?

393
00:21:33.734 --> 00:21:34.793
Three weeks.

394
00:21:35.102 --> 00:21:37.866
When my son had stitches
they said ten days.

395
00:21:38.073 --> 00:21:41.873
Really? Ten days. three weeks.
Any time in there.

396
00:21:48.717 --> 00:21:51.652
<i>We need an anesthesiologist to ICU.</i>

397
00:21:51.920 --> 00:21:53.751
<i>Please report to the ICU. stat.</i>

398
00:21:54.890 --> 00:21:57.882
250 mg Rocephin I.M. For the
man in Room 4...

399
00:21:58.093 --> 00:22:00.756
...and remind him to come back
in two days.

400
00:22:01.898 --> 00:22:03.797
Carol. are we out of oral
ampicillin?

401
00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:05.592
We ordered some yesterday.

402
00:22:05.801 --> 00:22:08.828
- Dr. Greene wants more Lasix.
- We were out an hour ago.

403
00:22:09.038 --> 00:22:11.438
Dr. Ross wants some PKU cards.

404
00:22:11.640 --> 00:22:14.235
No. He'll have to get
a blue-top from the baby.

405
00:22:14.444 --> 00:22:15.536
He says he can't.

406
00:22:17.180 --> 00:22:21.276
Are you sure that you don't have
a PKU card tucked away in...

407
00:22:21.484 --> 00:22:23.611
...that special stash of yours?

408
00:22:26.055 --> 00:22:27.750
Like this?

409
00:22:28.058 --> 00:22:32.357
I can always count on you.
Even if you do prefer football players.

410
00:22:32.563 --> 00:22:34.325
You had your chance.

411
00:22:34.530 --> 00:22:36.555
I was young. I was a fool!

412
00:22:37.301 --> 00:22:38.290
You're still a fool.

413
00:22:38.736 --> 00:22:40.966
What's the worst
paying medical specialty?

414
00:22:42.306 --> 00:22:45.298
- Pediatrics?
- You were right the first time.

415
00:22:49.346 --> 00:22:53.783
Carol. did that Lasix come up yet?
Because we need it now!

416
00:23:08.466 --> 00:23:12.129
Good morning. I'm Dr. Carter.
What seems to be the problem?

417
00:23:12.537 --> 00:23:16.132
What's it look like?
I shot myself in the freaking leg.

418
00:23:19.511 --> 00:23:22.071
- We'll fix you up.
- You guys keep saying that.

419
00:23:22.280 --> 00:23:24.943
But first. we have to start
a little IV.

420
00:23:25.151 --> 00:23:26.982
Just hurry it up. okay?

421
00:23:27.186 --> 00:23:28.448
Yes. sir.

422
00:23:31.424 --> 00:23:33.358
Oh. excuse me. Sorry.

423
00:23:38.331 --> 00:23:41.027
I wanted to belt her in the mouth.
I really did.

424
00:23:42.468 --> 00:23:44.766
Then I go and shoot myself in the leg.

425
00:23:45.038 --> 00:23:46.095
These things happen.

426
00:23:46.306 --> 00:23:49.707
I bet you see a lot
working in a place like this.

427
00:23:50.276 --> 00:23:51.834
Oh. yeah. All the time.

428
00:24:04.558 --> 00:24:07.686
You don't mind my asking.
have you done this before?

429
00:24:07.961 --> 00:24:10.192
I'd hate to tell you how often
I've done this.

430
00:24:11.665 --> 00:24:12.689
You'll feel a needle.

431
00:24:15.669 --> 00:24:17.035
Come on. it wasn't that bad.

432
00:24:18.272 --> 00:24:20.000
But we missed the vein.

433
00:24:20.408 --> 00:24:22.740
We have to try this one more time.

434
00:24:23.644 --> 00:24:26.135
My wife's not that bad.
We don't argue that much.

435
00:24:26.347 --> 00:24:29.213
Once in a while. In this case
it's lucky I didn't kill her.

436
00:24:29.417 --> 00:24:30.611
Oh. man!

437
00:24:31.452 --> 00:24:32.817
I'm afraid we missed again.

438
00:24:33.621 --> 00:24:34.883
We'll try one more time.

439
00:24:35.757 --> 00:24:38.556
You have very tough veins.

440
00:24:39.293 --> 00:24:40.761
My wife...

441
00:24:40.963 --> 00:24:43.022
...is a very beautiful woman.

442
00:24:44.066 --> 00:24:48.263
I'm not proud of beating up any woman.
Even when she's asking for it.

443
00:24:48.469 --> 00:24:52.031
I mean in this case. it's lucky
I didn't break her neck!

444
00:24:52.241 --> 00:24:53.572
I got it. Don't move.

445
00:24:54.410 --> 00:24:55.536
Don't move!

446
00:24:55.744 --> 00:24:57.871
It's in the vein. Do not move at all.

447
00:25:01.151 --> 00:25:04.017
There you go. officer.
You got yourself an IV!

448
00:25:04.486 --> 00:25:06.078
Everything's gonna be fine now.

449
00:25:06.956 --> 00:25:08.116
Can I move?

450
00:25:08.457 --> 00:25:09.856
Sure. move around.
You're fine.

451
00:25:10.959 --> 00:25:12.928
That's all I can do for the moment.

452
00:25:13.128 --> 00:25:15.859
They'll take you to X-ray.
then to surgery.

453
00:25:16.799 --> 00:25:20.201
- Surgery?
- But believe me...

454
00:25:20.737 --> 00:25:21.965
...the worst is over.

455
00:25:23.072 --> 00:25:24.437
This happened when you woke up?

456
00:25:24.641 --> 00:25:26.438
Yes. when I got out of bed.

457
00:25:26.643 --> 00:25:28.475
- Are you still seeing double now?
- No.

458
00:25:28.678 --> 00:25:30.738
- How many fingers?
- Three.

459
00:25:30.947 --> 00:25:33.415
- Have you had eye trouble before?
- No. never.

460
00:25:33.616 --> 00:25:35.380
Did you have pain while
seeing double?

461
00:25:35.586 --> 00:25:37.486
Headache?
Trouble with your balance?

462
00:25:37.688 --> 00:25:40.451
Funny taste in your mouth?
Flashing spots?

463
00:25:40.657 --> 00:25:45.061
- Weakness in limbs?
- No. none of those things. Never.

464
00:25:45.261 --> 00:25:47.856
I can call a neurologist
to go over you...

465
00:25:48.065 --> 00:25:49.895
...but that'll cost you $200.

466
00:25:50.100 --> 00:25:52.898
If you don't have any symptoms now.
I'd leave it alone.

467
00:25:53.405 --> 00:25:54.996
Come back if you have
more trouble.

468
00:25:56.006 --> 00:25:59.373
- Who's next?
- You're just saying that because I'm black.

469
00:25:59.577 --> 00:26:02.341
Trying to save you money.
I know you don't have insurance.

470
00:26:02.747 --> 00:26:05.215
You wouldn't say this
if I wasn't black.

471
00:26:05.416 --> 00:26:07.044
You're Jewish. right?

472
00:26:07.918 --> 00:26:12.754
Call a neuro consult for Mr. Ervin.
cc transient diplopia. and bill him.

473
00:26:24.336 --> 00:26:25.769
Hello. somebody! Hello!

474
00:26:25.971 --> 00:26:29.168
- What is it?
- I got a lady pregnant in my cab outside.

475
00:26:29.407 --> 00:26:31.273
Why'd you do that?

476
00:26:31.810 --> 00:26:32.902
We don't deliver here.

477
00:26:33.112 --> 00:26:35.306
You have to take her up to OB.

478
00:26:35.515 --> 00:26:38.211
She's having a baby whether you
deliver it or not.

479
00:26:39.652 --> 00:26:42.450
Hey. you busy?
Why don't you come with me?

480
00:26:43.523 --> 00:26:45.218
Get us an OB nurse.

481
00:26:46.760 --> 00:26:50.661
Okay. okay. ma'am.
Come on. Let's go. Let's get out.

482
00:26:50.863 --> 00:26:53.229
- You'll be fine.
- When did it start snowing?

483
00:26:54.033 --> 00:26:56.229
Come on. doctor. give me a hand!

484
00:26:56.435 --> 00:26:58.461
Up on the gurney. there you go.

485
00:26:58.671 --> 00:27:00.572
Is this your first child?

486
00:27:02.341 --> 00:27:04.435
Okay. let's go.

487
00:27:07.548 --> 00:27:09.140
It's starting. it's coming!

488
00:27:09.783 --> 00:27:12.479
Hold the head in. We don't
want her to deliver here.

489
00:27:12.686 --> 00:27:15.314
Put your hand between her legs
and hold the head in.

490
00:27:15.889 --> 00:27:18.016
Breathe. ma'am.
Blow through the pain.

491
00:27:18.225 --> 00:27:22.060
Get me Anesthesia. call the
pediatrician. Hook up those stirrups.

492
00:27:22.263 --> 00:27:23.627
You doing an episiotomy?

493
00:27:23.830 --> 00:27:25.957
I don't have time.
She's already crowning.

494
00:27:26.166 --> 00:27:28.829
Blow through the pain. ma'am.
Blow through the pain.

495
00:27:29.037 --> 00:27:30.765
Blow through the pain.
That's right.

496
00:27:30.972 --> 00:27:33.338
- What should I do?
- Just what you're doing.

497
00:27:33.541 --> 00:27:35.099
Is it snowing out there?

498
00:27:35.944 --> 00:27:38.572
When I'm done scrubbing.
I'll take over while you scrub.

499
00:27:39.213 --> 00:27:41.341
- Where's the OB resident?
- They're on call.

500
00:27:41.549 --> 00:27:42.743
You want a gown?

501
00:27:42.951 --> 00:27:44.179
I don't think I have time.

502
00:27:44.385 --> 00:27:47.116
I'm gonna have to catch this one
anyway I can.

503
00:27:47.322 --> 00:27:50.451
No kidding? All right. dear.
You'll be just fine.

504
00:27:50.659 --> 00:27:53.059
You just have to blow. okay? Blow.

505
00:27:53.261 --> 00:27:54.957
- Is it snowing?
- Yeah. it's snowing.

506
00:27:55.164 --> 00:27:57.689
Snowing on March 17th.
This is unbelievable.

507
00:27:57.900 --> 00:28:00.892
It's okay. ma'am.
You're going to be just fine.

508
00:28:01.337 --> 00:28:04.101
Let me take over. There we go.

509
00:28:04.306 --> 00:28:07.639
Ma'am. we're gonna push on
the next one. okay?

510
00:28:09.411 --> 00:28:12.176
One. two. three...

511
00:28:15.352 --> 00:28:17.080
One more. This is the one.

512
00:28:17.286 --> 00:28:20.279
And. push. push. push...

513
00:28:22.058 --> 00:28:23.252
One more push.

514
00:28:23.460 --> 00:28:24.825
We're gonna get him out.

515
00:28:25.028 --> 00:28:28.225
One. two. three. push.
Good!

516
00:28:28.431 --> 00:28:30.661
Shoulders are clear.

517
00:28:33.737 --> 00:28:35.967
You have a beautiful little boy.

518
00:28:37.041 --> 00:28:38.439
Clamp.

519
00:28:40.910 --> 00:28:42.138
There you go.

520
00:28:57.795 --> 00:28:59.092
He's a cutie-pie.

521
00:28:59.296 --> 00:29:00.696
You did a good job there.

522
00:29:10.474 --> 00:29:13.171
Dr. Carter. You have 3 sutures
waiting for you.

523
00:29:13.378 --> 00:29:16.575
You're not on medical services.
They don't need your help.

524
00:29:16.782 --> 00:29:18.147
Come on. let's get cracking.

525
00:29:33.331 --> 00:29:35.129
Patient: Martin. Jonathan.

526
00:29:35.333 --> 00:29:38.394
Anterior and lateral
right lower extremity.

527
00:29:38.604 --> 00:29:40.595
Femur articulation...

528
00:29:40.807 --> 00:29:44.436
...patella. tibia. fibula
all appear normal.

529
00:29:44.644 --> 00:29:47.272
There's a radiolucent density
in the soft tissue...

530
00:29:47.480 --> 00:29:49.471
...superficial to the fibula.

531
00:29:49.682 --> 00:29:51.843
A bullet is what it's called. Steve.

532
00:29:52.051 --> 00:29:55.418
There is no apparent fragmentation of
the foreign body.

533
00:29:55.621 --> 00:29:57.487
Distal tibia and fibula
all appear...

534
00:29:57.691 --> 00:29:59.886
- Come on. Steve!
...within normal limits.

535
00:30:00.094 --> 00:30:03.291
Impression: Foreign body in
the right lower extremity...

536
00:30:03.497 --> 00:30:06.260
...consistent with possible bullet.

537
00:30:07.134 --> 00:30:10.035
Is that it? Thank you.

538
00:30:10.504 --> 00:30:11.698
I'll take these.

539
00:30:11.905 --> 00:30:16.069
There's a guy with a bullet in
his leg who'd like to have it out.

540
00:30:20.748 --> 00:30:24.206
Sure you're not feeling any pain?
No pain here in your back?

541
00:30:24.719 --> 00:30:25.845
You know what?

542
00:30:26.054 --> 00:30:28.454
All you've got is
a fracture to your ankle.

543
00:30:28.655 --> 00:30:30.453
Everything else is fine.

544
00:30:30.658 --> 00:30:34.185
Now. what's the story. doc?
Do I get worker's comp?

545
00:30:34.429 --> 00:30:35.793
The story?

546
00:30:36.698 --> 00:30:38.529
The story is. you're still alive.

547
00:30:38.733 --> 00:30:40.792
Great. but I got a few bills and...

548
00:30:44.639 --> 00:30:47.164
There it is. nice and red.

549
00:30:47.510 --> 00:30:50.000
He has Otitis media.
He'll be fine.

550
00:30:50.913 --> 00:30:53.506
250 milligrams of oral amoxicillan.

551
00:30:53.715 --> 00:30:56.013
If he's not better tomorrow.
call me.

552
00:30:56.217 --> 00:30:58.152
All right? It was nice to see you.

553
00:30:58.353 --> 00:30:59.878
Bye. tiger.

554
00:31:01.223 --> 00:31:03.851
- He's very handsome.
- He knows it.

555
00:31:04.192 --> 00:31:07.959
We got a UA and a sed rate
for patient Rebecca Morton.

556
00:31:08.164 --> 00:31:09.825
M-O-R...

557
00:31:10.032 --> 00:31:12.331
What do you mean?
We sent this an hour ago!

558
00:31:12.535 --> 00:31:15.231
It's 1:40 and it was a stat
determination.

559
00:31:15.437 --> 00:31:17.405
What're you doing.
picking your noses?

560
00:31:17.606 --> 00:31:19.575
Chest pains two hours. question AMI.

561
00:31:19.775 --> 00:31:21.869
I will talk to you
any damn way I want to.

562
00:31:22.077 --> 00:31:23.544
If I sent for a stat chem...

563
00:31:23.747 --> 00:31:26.614
...I want it in an hour.
not sometime next month.

564
00:31:27.150 --> 00:31:29.744
Well. we're a little busy here too.

565
00:31:30.452 --> 00:31:34.014
When they start going to lunch
things will really slow down.

566
00:31:35.592 --> 00:31:38.322
- What do you want me to do?
- Go to lunch.

567
00:31:38.628 --> 00:31:40.493
I'm okay. if there's
something to do.

568
00:31:41.031 --> 00:31:42.521
Excuse me a minute.

569
00:31:48.071 --> 00:31:49.198
Don't be a hero.

570
00:31:49.406 --> 00:31:51.136
If I tell you to go to lunch. go.

571
00:31:51.342 --> 00:31:54.573
It's a long time before dinner.
and you may be too busy to eat.

572
00:31:54.779 --> 00:31:58.180
You never know how long till
your next meal. so eat when you can.

573
00:31:58.382 --> 00:32:02.011
Get the hell out of here.
And don't take more than half an hour.

574
00:32:13.699 --> 00:32:16.361
I'm Dr. Greene.
What's the trouble. Mrs. O'Rourke?

575
00:32:16.567 --> 00:32:18.263
I'm not Mrs. O'Rourke.

576
00:32:20.338 --> 00:32:21.532
Mrs. O'Rourke!

577
00:32:22.140 --> 00:32:24.608
Is there a Mrs. O'Rourke here?

578
00:32:36.422 --> 00:32:37.719
- Tyrone!
- What is it?

579
00:32:37.923 --> 00:32:39.515
Crack dealer. Took 5 shots.

580
00:32:39.726 --> 00:32:40.988
We need muscle in here!

581
00:32:41.194 --> 00:32:43.162
- He's just a kid.
- Thirteen.

582
00:32:43.363 --> 00:32:44.694
- Call security!
- Why?

583
00:32:44.898 --> 00:32:48.197
The other gang members
may come and finish him off.

584
00:32:52.505 --> 00:32:54.166
Let's keep it calm.
Here we go.

585
00:32:54.374 --> 00:32:58.435
This is Tracy Young in ER.
I need someone in Trauma Room 1.

586
00:33:04.584 --> 00:33:06.609
Surgical 2. Turn right and down.

587
00:33:06.819 --> 00:33:08.946
We have a motorcycle accident coming.

588
00:33:09.155 --> 00:33:11.453
- Wasn't wearing a helmet.
- Those are stat labs.

589
00:33:11.659 --> 00:33:15.254
I'll be across the street. Told
my wife I'd keep this appointment.

590
00:33:15.462 --> 00:33:16.690
Can Susan cover for me?

591
00:33:17.865 --> 00:33:18.923
No. not there!

592
00:33:19.133 --> 00:33:21.033
Surgical 2!

593
00:34:06.015 --> 00:34:08.175
I'm Dr. Greene to see Dr. Harris.

594
00:34:13.122 --> 00:34:15.181
<i>Everyone has a family. Mark.</i>

595
00:34:15.391 --> 00:34:18.326
My wife wants to shop. Kids grow up.

596
00:34:18.528 --> 00:34:22.089
You want private school. college.
You gotta think about that.

597
00:34:22.732 --> 00:34:27.032
Now. the office for our
next associate is here.

598
00:34:29.139 --> 00:34:33.303
As a junior man. you'll do all calls
and weekends for a year or so.

599
00:34:33.510 --> 00:34:34.499
Compensation...

600
00:34:34.678 --> 00:34:39.047
...you'll start out at 120.000 per year.
plus bonuses.

601
00:34:39.883 --> 00:34:43.944
The group has a condo in Jamaica
and one in Aspen. Do you ski?

602
00:34:44.154 --> 00:34:45.451
Haven't had the opportunity.

603
00:34:45.655 --> 00:34:48.022
You should. It's a great sport.

604
00:34:48.226 --> 00:34:52.925
Morgenstern tells me that you're
the sharpest guy ER ever had.

605
00:34:53.130 --> 00:34:56.259
But I'll tell you.
the ER is a young man's game.

606
00:34:56.467 --> 00:34:59.299
You think you're doing good.
but there's a lot to life...

607
00:34:59.504 --> 00:35:01.096
...especially this one.

608
00:35:01.305 --> 00:35:03.864
We find the practice
intellectually challenging...

609
00:35:04.075 --> 00:35:06.703
...so we send our physicians
to major conferences.

610
00:35:06.911 --> 00:35:10.746
Last year: Maui. Paris. Rome.

611
00:35:11.950 --> 00:35:16.785
We're proud to practice the best
possible medicine we can here.

612
00:35:17.890 --> 00:35:20.051
- Seems great.
- You like this?

613
00:35:20.259 --> 00:35:22.227
We had Prescott redesign it.

614
00:35:22.428 --> 00:35:26.091
We redesign every couple of years.
Keeps us looking fresh.

615
00:35:26.799 --> 00:35:27.788
Terrific.

616
00:35:28.000 --> 00:35:29.899
Do we have time for lunch?

617
00:35:30.102 --> 00:35:33.265
We'll go to the Crown Club.
They have a great porcini pasta.

618
00:35:33.472 --> 00:35:35.167
- I gotta get back.
- No oil!

619
00:35:36.542 --> 00:35:39.239
Melissa would you bring
Dr. Greene's coat?

620
00:35:39.445 --> 00:35:40.742
Maybe next week?

621
00:35:42.381 --> 00:35:44.782
- We'd love to have you.
- Thank you.

622
00:35:46.985 --> 00:35:49.784
Mrs. McCormick. how are you?

623
00:35:49.989 --> 00:35:54.323
I thought the Field Museum Ball
was wonderful!

624
00:35:54.860 --> 00:35:57.352
Margo loved the flower arrangements.

625
00:36:08.876 --> 00:36:10.843
Cheer up. doctor. it's only 3:00.

626
00:36:11.045 --> 00:36:13.343
Three o'clock.
I must be crazy. huh?

627
00:36:13.547 --> 00:36:15.377
That's a very good insight.

628
00:36:27.261 --> 00:36:28.626
When did it start raining?

629
00:36:36.637 --> 00:36:38.036
It's raining!

630
00:36:38.240 --> 00:36:40.230
It has been for an hour.

631
00:36:41.108 --> 00:36:43.770
- How's your new student?
- Very capable.

632
00:36:43.979 --> 00:36:45.310
Tough.

633
00:36:46.848 --> 00:36:49.874
So I hear you went up to
Harris' today.

634
00:36:50.085 --> 00:36:51.518
Did he offer you a job?

635
00:36:51.719 --> 00:36:55.157
Yeah. I think I have to go to
a lot of charity balls.

636
00:36:55.357 --> 00:36:57.154
There are worse things.

637
00:36:57.359 --> 00:36:58.917
I guess.

638
00:36:59.127 --> 00:37:00.458
Must be.

639
00:37:00.930 --> 00:37:04.331
What's this I hear about you
and that tech up on Surgical 4?

640
00:37:04.534 --> 00:37:06.525
- I'm a married man.
- So?

641
00:37:06.736 --> 00:37:09.795
- So whatever you heard is not true.
- All right.

642
00:37:10.006 --> 00:37:12.064
I heard that she was seriously cute.

643
00:37:12.275 --> 00:37:15.904
But you are faithful to your wife.
Is that what you're telling me?

644
00:37:17.246 --> 00:37:19.874
Why would you do something like that?

645
00:37:20.082 --> 00:37:22.449
Because I'm too tired
to do anything else.

646
00:37:28.658 --> 00:37:32.059
We'll know more when we have
the x-rays. How much do you smoke?

647
00:37:33.163 --> 00:37:35.131
Two. three packs a day sometimes.

648
00:37:35.332 --> 00:37:37.664
And how long have you been
doing this?

649
00:37:38.402 --> 00:37:40.369
Since I was about 14. I guess.

650
00:37:40.571 --> 00:37:43.131
- You really should stop that.
- I know.

651
00:37:43.807 --> 00:37:46.571
Excuse me.
You can put your clothes back on.

652
00:37:55.118 --> 00:37:58.246
Listen. I can't talk at work
unless it's... It is?

653
00:37:58.455 --> 00:38:01.084
Well. what...?

654
00:38:01.292 --> 00:38:04.455
No. I'm on all night.

655
00:38:04.662 --> 00:38:08.359
I get off tomorrow night at six.

656
00:38:08.566 --> 00:38:11.000
Paul. I thought we broke up.

657
00:38:11.669 --> 00:38:13.728
Oh. Paul. come on.

658
00:38:16.140 --> 00:38:17.903
Damn!

659
00:38:18.110 --> 00:38:22.945
What? No. not you. It's just.
I have to tell a patient something.

660
00:38:23.147 --> 00:38:27.517
Listen. is everything all right?
I'm sorry. but I just...

661
00:38:27.720 --> 00:38:30.985
Yeah. Okay. bye.

662
00:38:35.127 --> 00:38:37.391
We have your x-rays. Mr. Parker.

663
00:38:40.199 --> 00:38:43.464
You can see there's a density
in the right middle lobe.

664
00:38:44.003 --> 00:38:45.301
What does that mean?

665
00:38:45.505 --> 00:38:48.632
Something abnormal within
the structure of your lung.

666
00:38:48.842 --> 00:38:50.706
- In my lung?
- That's right.

667
00:38:53.178 --> 00:38:55.203
- What is it?
- It could be...

668
00:38:55.414 --> 00:38:59.146
...an infiltrate. a dense area
of tissue from an old infection.

669
00:38:59.352 --> 00:39:00.944
Perhaps an inhaled foreign body.

670
00:39:01.154 --> 00:39:04.554
It could be a granuloma.
It could be a lot of things.

671
00:39:07.594 --> 00:39:10.119
- What do you think it is?
- There's no way to know.

672
00:39:10.331 --> 00:39:12.799
You'll need
a bronchoscopy and possibly...

673
00:39:12.999 --> 00:39:14.557
...exploratory surgery.

674
00:39:15.302 --> 00:39:17.998
I understand. but what do you
think in the meantime?

675
00:39:18.572 --> 00:39:21.335
You should consider it
potentially serious.

676
00:39:26.480 --> 00:39:27.469
So I got cancer.

677
00:39:27.682 --> 00:39:31.413
I'm not saying that.
We don't know anything for sure.

678
00:39:31.619 --> 00:39:33.484
Let me explain something to you.

679
00:39:33.688 --> 00:39:35.849
I'm 40. I have a wife
and 3 children...

680
00:39:36.057 --> 00:39:37.388
...a house not paid for...

681
00:39:37.592 --> 00:39:39.753
...and a mother whose house
isn't paid for.

682
00:39:39.961 --> 00:39:41.223
I have responsibilities.

683
00:39:41.429 --> 00:39:44.193
So I need to know.
I need to know what you think.

684
00:39:44.399 --> 00:39:47.732
You should regard your condition
as very serious...

685
00:39:47.936 --> 00:39:49.698
...but await a final determination.

686
00:39:49.904 --> 00:39:51.805
I don't understand the problem.

687
00:39:52.274 --> 00:39:54.242
Are you afraid to tell me the truth?

688
00:39:57.546 --> 00:40:01.004
Your history of coughing blood.
weight loss...

689
00:40:01.650 --> 00:40:04.950
...and this x-ray
is suggestive of cancer.

690
00:40:05.153 --> 00:40:09.318
But the diagnosis is not confirmed.
and it may be something else.

691
00:40:09.525 --> 00:40:12.652
And we shouldn't jump to any
conclusions until we know.

692
00:40:12.862 --> 00:40:14.022
That's what I think.

693
00:40:19.869 --> 00:40:21.359
How long do I have?

694
00:40:29.612 --> 00:40:30.944
Six months to a year.

695
00:40:41.392 --> 00:40:42.950
Do I have six months for sure?

696
00:40:44.161 --> 00:40:46.129
No. not for sure.

697
00:40:52.703 --> 00:40:56.469
I was wondering because I always
wanted to take my wife to Nassau.

698
00:40:56.774 --> 00:40:59.243
We talked about it.
but we never did it.

699
00:40:59.444 --> 00:41:04.380
I just figured. spring's coming.
it's getting too late to go to Nassau.

700
00:41:04.581 --> 00:41:08.746
She always wanted a suntan in the
winter to show off to the neighbors.

701
00:41:09.319 --> 00:41:10.308
I understand.

702
00:41:14.859 --> 00:41:16.520
So I guess I'd better go.

703
00:41:16.728 --> 00:41:20.630
Summer will be here before you know it.
so I better go soon. huh?

704
00:41:21.366 --> 00:41:23.096
Doctor. I want to thank you.

705
00:41:23.902 --> 00:41:27.999
I want to thank you for your help
and for being straight with me.

706
00:41:31.943 --> 00:41:34.104
I guess I don't have to quit smoking.

707
00:41:54.968 --> 00:41:58.768
Mr. Parker. if there's one thing
you learn in my job...

708
00:41:58.971 --> 00:42:00.997
...it's that nothing is certain.

709
00:42:01.675 --> 00:42:05.304
Nothing that seems very bad
and nothing that seems very good.

710
00:42:05.979 --> 00:42:08.106
Nothing is certain.

711
00:42:08.715 --> 00:42:09.841
Nothing.

712
00:42:32.172 --> 00:42:33.538
I'm sorry.

713
00:42:57.633 --> 00:42:58.861
Good evening.

714
00:42:59.067 --> 00:43:01.228
How's it going tonight. Mrs. Raskin?

715
00:43:01.436 --> 00:43:05.167
Timmy. I have a problem
that requires medical attention.

716
00:43:05.374 --> 00:43:08.207
See Dr. Greene.
He's on duty tonight.

717
00:43:09.478 --> 00:43:11.037
Dr. Greene!

718
00:43:11.247 --> 00:43:12.770
How nice!

719
00:43:14.249 --> 00:43:15.979
- Good evening.
- How you doing?

720
00:43:16.184 --> 00:43:18.244
He says he doesn't drink. Then...

721
00:43:18.453 --> 00:43:22.184
I require medical attention.
Dr. Greene.

722
00:43:22.425 --> 00:43:24.290
Give me a minute. Chris.

723
00:43:24.493 --> 00:43:25.551
Yes. Mrs. Raskin?

724
00:43:25.762 --> 00:43:29.289
I have this troublesome...

725
00:43:29.465 --> 00:43:30.454
...hangnail.

726
00:43:30.667 --> 00:43:33.261
- Mrs. Raskin.
- I'm afraid it may be infected.

727
00:43:33.469 --> 00:43:37.371
If we treat you. it's gonna
cost you $ 180. You do know that?

728
00:43:37.574 --> 00:43:39.064
I wish you'd do it for me.

729
00:43:39.376 --> 00:43:41.571
You're such a nice young doctor...

730
00:43:41.779 --> 00:43:44.976
...and I do appreciate
your taking the time.

731
00:43:49.419 --> 00:43:51.047
We'll handle this in the lab.

732
00:43:51.255 --> 00:43:54.224
The lab? Oh. gracious!

733
00:43:55.359 --> 00:43:57.884
I had no idea how complicated it was!

734
00:43:58.095 --> 00:44:00.188
I'll be excising
Mrs. Raskin's hangnail.

735
00:44:00.364 --> 00:44:01.422
I'll stand back.

736
00:44:01.599 --> 00:44:03.897
Well. at my age.
you can't be too careful.

737
00:44:04.101 --> 00:44:06.433
Please have a seat. Mrs. Raskin.

738
00:44:06.671 --> 00:44:08.161
Thank you.

739
00:44:09.307 --> 00:44:13.208
Dr. Greene. you look tired.
How have you been?

740
00:44:13.411 --> 00:44:14.537
Fine. thanks.

741
00:44:14.746 --> 00:44:18.614
And your wife? Is she still
studying for her bar exam?

742
00:44:18.817 --> 00:44:21.786
Next month.
We won't see much of each other.

743
00:44:21.987 --> 00:44:23.454
This alcohol may feel cold.

744
00:44:23.755 --> 00:44:27.191
- Mark. you got time for coffee?
- In half an hour.

745
00:44:29.495 --> 00:44:32.554
She's very cute.
She work here at the hospital?

746
00:44:32.765 --> 00:44:33.959
She's a resident.

747
00:44:35.600 --> 00:44:38.764
Did I tell you
my sister got remarried?

748
00:44:39.772 --> 00:44:42.297
How long has it been
since I've seen you?

749
00:44:43.142 --> 00:44:45.406
Just a week or so.

750
00:44:46.379 --> 00:44:48.870
- Here we go.
- Oh. don't make such a fuss!

751
00:44:51.083 --> 00:44:53.177
Thank you. Dr. Greene.

752
00:44:55.054 --> 00:44:57.147
Now. you be a good boy...

753
00:44:57.590 --> 00:45:00.025
...and go home to your wife.

754
00:45:03.930 --> 00:45:06.591
- Another day. another dollar.
- Good night. Timmy.

755
00:45:06.800 --> 00:45:08.199
- See you.
- Good night.

756
00:45:08.402 --> 00:45:09.699
Hey. Red.

757
00:45:10.203 --> 00:45:11.898
- Hey. Tim.
- How you doing?

758
00:45:12.105 --> 00:45:13.970
- I'm good.
- Yeah? Good.

759
00:45:14.174 --> 00:45:15.402
Ready to work.

760
00:45:17.878 --> 00:45:19.709
- Can you get some...
- Sorry. I'm off.

761
00:45:19.913 --> 00:45:21.506
- I forgot. See you.
- Good night.

762
00:45:21.716 --> 00:45:25.947
In 3. the lady with pulmonary edema
gets Lasix and a nitroglycerin drip.

763
00:45:26.154 --> 00:45:29.350
In 4. there's some kid.
Dr. Ross is looking after him.

764
00:45:29.557 --> 00:45:33.391
Five. there's a question pulmonary
embolism. Labs are coming.

765
00:45:33.660 --> 00:45:35.151
I need 2 grams chloramphenicol.

766
00:45:35.363 --> 00:45:38.264
You're gonna have to get it
from the next shift.

767
00:45:41.736 --> 00:45:43.499
- See you tomorrow.
- Good night.

768
00:45:43.705 --> 00:45:45.195
Malik needs chloramphenicol.

769
00:45:45.407 --> 00:45:47.169
- Coming right up.
- All right.

770
00:45:49.043 --> 00:45:50.908
- Good night.
- See you.

771
00:45:51.113 --> 00:45:52.807
See you guys tomorrow.

772
00:46:07.196 --> 00:46:10.632
Come on. it's not that bad.
It's a very minor cut.

773
00:46:10.833 --> 00:46:14.098
- Three stitches.
- It's not the cut!

774
00:46:14.303 --> 00:46:16.135
It's the car.

775
00:46:16.572 --> 00:46:18.938
I smashed the car.

776
00:46:21.510 --> 00:46:25.504
I wasn't supposed to drive it.
and I took the keys...

777
00:46:25.715 --> 00:46:27.945
...and I smashed it up.

778
00:46:28.417 --> 00:46:30.818
And it was brand-new!

779
00:46:31.020 --> 00:46:34.148
My father loves that car.

780
00:46:35.158 --> 00:46:38.389
Well. it might not be
as bad as you think.

781
00:46:40.730 --> 00:46:43.325
It was a brand-new Cadillac...

782
00:46:44.234 --> 00:46:46.566
...with power steering...

783
00:46:46.871 --> 00:46:48.998
...and air conditioning.

784
00:46:50.040 --> 00:46:52.531
Oh. God! He'll kill me.

785
00:46:52.743 --> 00:46:56.644
It was the first new car he ever had!

786
00:47:06.057 --> 00:47:07.217
Suzanne.

787
00:47:10.194 --> 00:47:12.389
- Oh. my God!
- Oh. Daddy.

788
00:47:14.965 --> 00:47:16.627
Could we not move. please?

789
00:47:18.135 --> 00:47:21.162
- Is she gonna be all right?
- She's gonna be fine.

790
00:47:22.407 --> 00:47:23.874
Oh. honey.

791
00:47:25.343 --> 00:47:26.367
Daddy...

792
00:47:26.578 --> 00:47:28.739
...I trashed the car.

793
00:47:30.015 --> 00:47:31.482
It's all right.

794
00:47:31.683 --> 00:47:34.174
The important thing is
that you're okay.

795
00:47:38.290 --> 00:47:39.723
What car?

796
00:47:43.496 --> 00:47:44.484
The Caddy?

797
00:47:45.564 --> 00:47:46.930
Daddy. I'm so sorry.

798
00:47:47.133 --> 00:47:49.499
You totaled my new Seville?

799
00:47:57.777 --> 00:47:59.836
My new Cadillac!

800
00:48:18.832 --> 00:48:19.958
It doesn't matter.

801
00:48:23.437 --> 00:48:24.426
It doesn't matter.

802
00:48:27.274 --> 00:48:29.265
You have 6 in backup.
That's not good.

803
00:48:29.476 --> 00:48:31.967
The worst is yet to come.
Let's move. huh?

804
00:48:37.218 --> 00:48:38.775
Who was that idiot?

805
00:48:40.321 --> 00:48:41.345
Why'd he do it?

806
00:48:41.556 --> 00:48:43.786
I don't know.
He just swallowed it.

807
00:48:43.992 --> 00:48:46.119
- Jimmy. why'd you do it?
- Because.

808
00:48:46.327 --> 00:48:47.760
You see? He's impossible!

809
00:48:47.962 --> 00:48:49.657
Here's the KUB.

810
00:48:51.733 --> 00:48:53.291
There it is. all right.

811
00:48:54.502 --> 00:48:56.164
You mean it's in his stomach?

812
00:48:56.372 --> 00:48:58.499
- You said he swallowed it.
- What do I do?

813
00:48:58.707 --> 00:49:00.834
Check his stools.
He'll probably pass it.

814
00:49:01.043 --> 00:49:04.570
I mean. how do I get into my house?
I'm locked out.

815
00:49:06.615 --> 00:49:08.549
You don't have another key?

816
00:49:08.851 --> 00:49:11.251
- It's not funny.
- I'm sorry.

817
00:49:16.659 --> 00:49:19.959
It's possible to become pregnant
without actual penetration.

818
00:49:20.162 --> 00:49:23.097
- Just by fooling around.
- I'm not pregnant.

819
00:49:23.300 --> 00:49:25.928
It's important you tell me
why you think you may be.

820
00:49:26.101 --> 00:49:27.091
No reason.

821
00:49:27.636 --> 00:49:30.401
If you are. you might
have an ectopic pregnancy...

822
00:49:30.607 --> 00:49:32.871
...and you'd need
surgery right away.

823
00:49:33.176 --> 00:49:35.974
It's serious. It could be
a matter of life and death.

824
00:49:36.179 --> 00:49:37.407
I'm not pregnant.

825
00:49:40.583 --> 00:49:42.346
Excuse me for one second.

826
00:49:42.686 --> 00:49:44.483
- How old?
- She's 13.

827
00:49:44.688 --> 00:49:48.021
She's got pain in her lower left
side and she's not pregnant?

828
00:49:48.758 --> 00:49:50.556
Okay. let's see.

829
00:49:56.032 --> 00:49:59.230
Hello. Miss Murphy.
I'm Dr. Benton.

830
00:49:59.770 --> 00:50:02.102
How long has it been
since your last period?

831
00:50:03.474 --> 00:50:06.409
- I don't know.
- Just think back. Tell me roughly.

832
00:50:10.481 --> 00:50:11.641
It was after Christmas.

833
00:50:13.318 --> 00:50:15.376
So it's been a few months.

834
00:50:15.754 --> 00:50:17.779
I guess so.
I haven't paid attention.

835
00:50:19.890 --> 00:50:21.449
You've had sexual intercourse?

836
00:50:26.465 --> 00:50:27.454
Yes.

837
00:50:29.634 --> 00:50:30.623
Dr. Carter...

838
00:50:32.637 --> 00:50:34.298
...it's an ectopic pregnancy...

839
00:50:34.506 --> 00:50:38.442
...and she needs to be scheduled
for ultrasound and surgery right away.

840
00:50:47.052 --> 00:50:48.486
How'd it go?

841
00:50:48.688 --> 00:50:52.817
You know what Harris' office is like.
It's like a nightclub or something.

842
00:50:53.026 --> 00:50:55.152
- He offered you a job?
- Yeah.

843
00:50:55.628 --> 00:50:57.960
- But I don't know.
- You don't wanna do it.

844
00:50:58.164 --> 00:51:00.792
It doesn't seem
like real medicine to me.

845
00:51:01.000 --> 00:51:03.935
- So what's the problem?
- You know what the problem is.

846
00:51:04.137 --> 00:51:05.605
Jennifer?

847
00:51:07.808 --> 00:51:09.832
You can't live your life
for someone else.

848
00:51:10.044 --> 00:51:11.772
- I know.
- Especially a lawyer.

849
00:51:12.045 --> 00:51:15.208
- She's not a lawyer yet.
- It's gotta be your life.

850
00:51:15.415 --> 00:51:17.384
It is. It's just...

851
00:51:17.583 --> 00:51:20.348
She keeps talking about
how she doesn't see me anymore.

852
00:51:20.654 --> 00:51:23.350
Well. she probably never does.
I never see Paul.

853
00:51:23.556 --> 00:51:25.047
I thought you guys broke up.

854
00:51:25.259 --> 00:51:27.193
Well. we did. But...

855
00:51:27.828 --> 00:51:29.090
...you know.

856
00:51:29.297 --> 00:51:30.388
Yeah.

857
00:51:43.178 --> 00:51:45.042
Yeah. yeah. Right away.

858
00:51:45.713 --> 00:51:47.112
Come on. we gotta go.

859
00:51:47.314 --> 00:51:48.680
We gotta go.

860
00:51:48.883 --> 00:51:50.316
Mark. what?

861
00:52:04.834 --> 00:52:06.232
Did you hear?

862
00:52:06.869 --> 00:52:08.802
Yeah. She's on her way.

863
00:52:09.938 --> 00:52:11.372
It's incredible.

864
00:52:11.574 --> 00:52:14.941
I don't know how this happened...

865
00:52:15.578 --> 00:52:17.671
...to her. of all people.

866
00:52:20.449 --> 00:52:21.814
I don't know.

867
00:52:26.123 --> 00:52:28.523
Okay. people.
Let's break it up.

868
00:52:28.724 --> 00:52:31.249
There's lots to do.
Let's get back to work.

869
00:52:37.834 --> 00:52:39.961
Come on.
What do you expect to see?

870
00:52:43.573 --> 00:52:45.768
Hey. let's get back to work!

871
00:52:47.077 --> 00:52:49.705
Go in here. Head first.

872
00:52:54.251 --> 00:52:56.651
My God. it is Hathaway!

873
00:53:01.158 --> 00:53:04.128
All right. move her on three.
One. two. three.

874
00:53:05.863 --> 00:53:09.026
Let's get her clothes off.
Let's go. let's go!

875
00:53:17.309 --> 00:53:18.469
Let's go.

876
00:53:22.313 --> 00:53:23.780
Call Respiratory.

877
00:53:24.982 --> 00:53:25.971
What'd she take?

878
00:53:26.251 --> 00:53:29.652
I don't know.
She went into the medicine cabinet.

879
00:53:30.822 --> 00:53:32.517
You have no idea what she took?

880
00:53:34.091 --> 00:53:37.858
I want a drug screen. two milligrams
of Narcan and an amp of D50.

881
00:53:38.063 --> 00:53:39.758
- You wanna pump her?
- Yep.

882
00:53:45.137 --> 00:53:47.537
Marie. call Neuro.
Call the nursing supervisor.

883
00:53:47.739 --> 00:53:49.173
Did you call her family?

884
00:53:49.375 --> 00:53:51.366
I don't know her family.

885
00:53:51.578 --> 00:53:53.603
- Why'd she do it?
- It doesn't matter why.

886
00:53:53.813 --> 00:53:57.510
We don't ask that about other ODs
and we don't ask it about this one.

887
00:54:27.548 --> 00:54:29.482
I want blood gas and electrolytes.

888
00:54:30.184 --> 00:54:32.584
- How hypotensive is she?
- 80 over 60.

889
00:54:32.920 --> 00:54:35.481
- Did she have anything to drink?
- A Scotch.

890
00:54:35.689 --> 00:54:38.385
- More than one?
- I don't know. Maybe.

891
00:54:40.195 --> 00:54:42.094
What are you people
standing around for?

892
00:54:43.498 --> 00:54:46.262
Do the arterial stick.
She got a Babinski?

893
00:54:46.700 --> 00:54:47.689
Yeah. positive.

894
00:54:52.641 --> 00:54:55.542
- How's the oxygen?
- Fifteen liters and running.

895
00:55:07.922 --> 00:55:10.447
Morgenstern's on his way.
Her serum barb is 45.

896
00:55:11.259 --> 00:55:13.921
- Is that a mistake?
- Repeated twice.

897
00:55:19.001 --> 00:55:21.731
Close the curtain.
This isn't a show here. people.

898
00:55:36.519 --> 00:55:38.181
And what's the nature of the...

899
00:55:38.388 --> 00:55:39.786
I see.

900
00:55:40.990 --> 00:55:44.687
Call Dr. Benton. We got a shotgun
wound to the chest coming in.

901
00:55:46.029 --> 00:55:47.155
What a night!

902
00:55:47.364 --> 00:55:49.832
Gas distention. distal
to the duodenum is...

903
00:55:50.033 --> 00:55:51.261
Call the O.R.

904
00:55:51.468 --> 00:55:53.936
Impression: Acute small
bowel obstruction.

905
00:55:54.137 --> 00:55:56.037
This is a surgical candidate.

906
00:55:56.240 --> 00:56:00.175
Oh. you guys are incredible.
What would we do without you?

907
00:56:00.410 --> 00:56:05.178
It's nice to see you. Peter.
Man of many talents. all unproven.

908
00:56:10.121 --> 00:56:12.453
We get a new barbiturate level yet?

909
00:56:13.023 --> 00:56:14.651
It just came back.

910
00:56:14.859 --> 00:56:16.656
It's still 45.

911
00:56:20.398 --> 00:56:23.493
<i>Pupils: Mid-range and sluggish.
BP: 90 over 70.</i>

912
00:56:24.969 --> 00:56:28.803
We just got her barbiturate level.
It's 45 micrograms per milliliter.

913
00:56:29.241 --> 00:56:33.507
She's intubated and we're getting
her ready for hemoperfusion.

914
00:56:33.712 --> 00:56:36.680
But if she's decerebrating...
You know the question.

915
00:56:36.881 --> 00:56:39.680
Should we be trying
any of this at all?

916
00:56:39.885 --> 00:56:41.147
It doesn't look hopeful.

917
00:56:41.353 --> 00:56:44.345
But for the morale of the unit.
we gotta do everything.

918
00:56:44.556 --> 00:56:46.387
I mean. she was...

919
00:56:47.126 --> 00:56:48.218
...is...

920
00:56:48.794 --> 00:56:50.820
...very popular.

921
00:56:55.101 --> 00:56:59.060
The unit's looking to you. Mark.
You set the tone.

922
00:57:03.877 --> 00:57:06.539
She was one of us.
We loved her. We worked with her.

923
00:57:06.746 --> 00:57:08.441
Now something's happened to her.

924
00:57:08.647 --> 00:57:13.210
It makes us feel guilty and angry
and scares the hell out of us.

925
00:57:13.520 --> 00:57:17.581
But we take care of her.
and then we go on with our jobs.

926
00:57:20.727 --> 00:57:22.991
You set the tone. Mark.

927
00:57:23.664 --> 00:57:25.188
You get the unit through this.

928
00:57:26.434 --> 00:57:27.594
I'm fine.

929
00:57:30.504 --> 00:57:32.665
Call me if anything happens.

930
00:57:35.810 --> 00:57:37.334
Anything at all.

931
00:57:52.660 --> 00:57:55.255
- She really did it. didn't she?
- Yeah. she did.

932
00:57:55.497 --> 00:57:58.193
- She seemed okay today.
- Yeah. she seemed fine.

933
00:57:58.400 --> 00:58:00.265
She was making jokes.

934
00:58:00.702 --> 00:58:04.229
Everything was great. She was funny.
She was joking like always.

935
00:58:04.840 --> 00:58:06.398
She was great.

936
00:58:09.644 --> 00:58:11.635
Go get some coffee. Doug.

937
00:58:56.960 --> 00:58:58.951
Come on. Let's get him up.

938
00:58:59.162 --> 00:59:01.154
Alrighty. Good. good.

939
00:59:02.333 --> 00:59:05.301
A knife wound.
I thought it was a gunshot wound.

940
00:59:05.502 --> 00:59:07.164
Excuse me.
I feel a little...

941
00:59:07.371 --> 00:59:10.863
I didn't need you anyway.
Notify the O.R. Let's get a room.

942
00:59:11.074 --> 00:59:13.235
Move him out.
Here we go. buddy.

943
00:59:17.015 --> 00:59:18.880
Jerry. hold that?

944
00:59:37.503 --> 00:59:38.993
Feeling better?

945
00:59:41.739 --> 00:59:45.506
I'll be okay in a minute.
It just got to me all of a sudden.

946
00:59:46.444 --> 00:59:47.969
Keep your head down.

947
00:59:48.213 --> 00:59:50.613
There's no rush. Just relax.

948
00:59:51.483 --> 00:59:53.917
It stopped raining.

949
00:59:57.756 --> 00:59:59.781
I thought I was going to be sick.

950
01:00:01.026 --> 01:00:02.015
I'm sorry.

951
01:00:02.227 --> 01:00:04.093
Don't ever say you're sorry.

952
01:00:05.464 --> 01:00:06.989
There's two kinds of doctors.

953
01:00:08.134 --> 01:00:10.034
Those who get rid
of their feelings...

954
01:00:10.235 --> 01:00:12.329
...and those who keep them.

955
01:00:13.907 --> 01:00:17.001
If you're gonna keep your feelings.
you'll get sick sometimes.

956
01:00:17.211 --> 01:00:19.007
That's just how it works.

957
01:00:20.347 --> 01:00:22.247
Keep your head down.

958
01:00:28.021 --> 01:00:29.420
People come in here...

959
01:00:29.623 --> 01:00:34.083
...and they're sick. dying
and bleeding...

960
01:00:34.295 --> 01:00:36.228
...and they need our help.

961
01:00:37.765 --> 01:00:40.427
Helping them is
more important than how we feel.

962
01:00:44.772 --> 01:00:47.468
But it's still a pain
in the ass sometimes.

963
01:00:50.212 --> 01:00:54.545
Sometimes I just want to quit
and do something else.

964
01:01:05.527 --> 01:01:07.620
Why don't you take
a few more minutes.

965
01:01:08.764 --> 01:01:09.753
By the way...

966
01:01:10.832 --> 01:01:13.824
...I was in medical school
with Benton.

967
01:01:14.369 --> 01:01:17.635
He used to get sick all the time.

968
01:01:18.775 --> 01:01:20.800
So don't let him give you any crap.

969
01:01:22.844 --> 01:01:23.833
You'll be fine.

970
01:01:40.130 --> 01:01:42.825
<i>Steven Howard has played
behind Damon.</i>

971
01:01:43.032 --> 01:01:46.992
<i>He'll have to come out
and take that ball away from him...</i>

972
01:02:10.027 --> 01:02:11.426
What's the score?

973
01:02:12.362 --> 01:02:13.352
De Paul is down.

974
01:02:16.266 --> 01:02:17.255
You okay?

975
01:02:18.368 --> 01:02:19.358
Good.

976
01:02:20.905 --> 01:02:23.031
Don't worry about
what happened out there.

977
01:02:24.676 --> 01:02:26.769
Just don't make a habit of it.

978
01:02:48.367 --> 01:02:52.463
She's been on dialysis for three hours.
She's still comatose.

979
01:02:52.671 --> 01:02:55.765
She took short-acting agents.
She knew what she was doing.

980
01:02:55.975 --> 01:02:58.603
- Has the family been notified?
- I think so.

981
01:02:58.811 --> 01:03:02.043
- Is she covered on the hospital policy?
- As far as I know.

982
01:03:02.248 --> 01:03:04.478
Has anyone talked to the press office?

983
01:03:04.683 --> 01:03:06.413
This is bad publicity.

984
01:03:06.620 --> 01:03:10.386
Some damn TV network will try
to make a sentimental movie about her.

985
01:03:10.589 --> 01:03:12.989
I'll get on it.
Anybody know why she did it?

986
01:03:13.193 --> 01:03:15.718
No one knows.
Her fiancé didn't know anything.

987
01:03:15.929 --> 01:03:18.227
They're supposed
to get married in June.

988
01:03:26.306 --> 01:03:27.534
Who's next?

989
01:03:27.741 --> 01:03:29.402
I am. doctor.

990
01:03:35.049 --> 01:03:38.109
Now lean forward.
You feeling any pain?

991
01:03:38.319 --> 01:03:40.651
It's better when I lean forward.

992
01:03:41.989 --> 01:03:43.957
Lydia. could I borrow your pen?

993
01:03:46.561 --> 01:03:49.860
Mr. Larkowsky. I'm going
to admit you to the hospital...

994
01:03:50.064 --> 01:03:52.055
...and start you on a medical regimen.

995
01:03:52.266 --> 01:03:55.430
There's some question in my mind
whether that's necessary...

996
01:03:55.636 --> 01:03:57.968
...but it's better
to be safe than sorry.

997
01:04:02.677 --> 01:04:03.905
What is it?

998
01:04:07.683 --> 01:04:08.877
What's the matter?

999
01:04:09.685 --> 01:04:13.018
- You don't have to hide the truth from me.
- The truth?

1000
01:04:13.222 --> 01:04:15.623
I know you're being nice.
but you can tell me.

1001
01:04:15.824 --> 01:04:17.689
It's okay.
I want to know the truth.

1002
01:04:18.794 --> 01:04:23.026
You have a duodenal ulcer
with complicating pancreatitis.

1003
01:04:23.232 --> 01:04:27.260
Rather mild pancreatitis. judging
from the lab figures. That's all.

1004
01:04:28.338 --> 01:04:29.929
Come on. You can tell me.

1005
01:04:31.574 --> 01:04:33.700
You don't have cancer. Mr. Larkowsky.

1006
01:04:37.647 --> 01:04:40.411
I knew it. I knew it!
It's cancer.

1007
01:04:40.617 --> 01:04:43.017
You were hiding it.

1008
01:04:45.688 --> 01:04:48.418
Every person that comes
into this hospital...

1009
01:04:48.626 --> 01:04:51.458
...whether they have
a heart attack or a skin rash...

1010
01:04:51.661 --> 01:04:53.220
...everybody worries about cancer.

1011
01:04:53.630 --> 01:04:55.326
You don't have cancer.

1012
01:04:55.532 --> 01:04:58.228
I swear to you.
You do not have cancer.

1013
01:05:02.806 --> 01:05:03.795
It's not cancer?

1014
01:05:05.609 --> 01:05:07.907
You have an ulcer
which flared up today...

1015
01:05:08.112 --> 01:05:11.138
...because you went to a party
and drank and smoked.

1016
01:05:11.548 --> 01:05:14.346
Both of which
you're gonna have to quit.

1017
01:05:17.588 --> 01:05:20.854
- Quit smoking and drinking?
- Yeah. that's right.

1018
01:05:22.159 --> 01:05:25.391
Quit smoking and drinking?
What. are you kidding me?

1019
01:05:46.084 --> 01:05:49.213
- We'll have to get x-rays on him.
- Right away. doctor.

1020
01:05:49.421 --> 01:05:51.014
How did this happen?

1021
01:05:51.957 --> 01:05:53.289
He fell out of his crib.

1022
01:05:55.360 --> 01:05:57.727
He fell out of his crib?

1023
01:05:59.265 --> 01:06:01.358
He was crying all night.
so I came here.

1024
01:06:01.567 --> 01:06:03.364
I bet he was.
When did he fall?

1025
01:06:03.570 --> 01:06:05.868
I don't know.
I don't want to get into trouble.

1026
01:06:06.072 --> 01:06:08.506
- Your son has multiple contusions.
- He's not my son.

1027
01:06:08.708 --> 01:06:11.644
- Whatever your relationship is...
- I'm his babysitter!

1028
01:06:20.821 --> 01:06:22.948
This child has been beaten.

1029
01:06:28.495 --> 01:06:32.693
- I'm gonna call Children Services.
- Please! I'll get into trouble.

1030
01:06:32.899 --> 01:06:34.299
Stay here.

1031
01:06:34.868 --> 01:06:36.427
Yes. doctor.

1032
01:06:44.879 --> 01:06:46.676
I don't believe this.

1033
01:06:46.881 --> 01:06:49.748
You want to make a guess
on the diagnosis of this one?

1034
01:06:55.691 --> 01:06:57.555
I burnt my legs.

1035
01:06:58.060 --> 01:06:59.084
I see.

1036
01:06:59.761 --> 01:07:00.750
It's not funny.

1037
01:07:01.095 --> 01:07:04.360
If you'll just come with me.
I'll take your name.

1038
01:07:04.565 --> 01:07:05.554
<i>College student?</i>

1039
01:07:06.969 --> 01:07:07.957
<i>Sacred Heart.</i>

1040
01:07:08.504 --> 01:07:10.300
And how'd this happen?

1041
01:07:10.706 --> 01:07:13.937
I was pouring hot water
into the sink and it splashed.

1042
01:07:14.410 --> 01:07:16.469
It's not bad.
First- degree burns.

1043
01:07:16.678 --> 01:07:19.738
There's no blistering.
and there won't be any scarring.

1044
01:07:20.617 --> 01:07:22.481
It's very sensitive skin.

1045
01:07:23.852 --> 01:07:25.411
Your touch is nice.

1046
01:07:25.621 --> 01:07:29.352
This medication will make
you feel a lot better.

1047
01:07:30.526 --> 01:07:32.790
Your fingers are very long.

1048
01:07:34.264 --> 01:07:36.254
Long and strong.

1049
01:07:38.134 --> 01:07:41.365
I wanted to change first
and put on some new underpants.

1050
01:07:42.605 --> 01:07:45.073
I knew you'd be seeing my underpants.

1051
01:07:46.576 --> 01:07:47.634
And touching them.

1052
01:07:50.013 --> 01:07:54.177
You'll want to keep these bandages
very dry for a day or so.

1053
01:07:55.118 --> 01:07:58.952
Don't take any showers or baths.
Just a sponge bath.

1054
01:08:00.023 --> 01:08:01.285
Why is that nurse here?

1055
01:08:01.525 --> 01:08:02.685
Hospital policy.

1056
01:08:02.893 --> 01:08:05.361
She's not assisting.
She doesn't have to be here.

1057
01:08:08.198 --> 01:08:09.291
Are you afraid of me?

1058
01:08:10.334 --> 01:08:12.996
You're gonna be just fine
in a few days.

1059
01:08:23.381 --> 01:08:24.870
Thanks. Lydia.

1060
01:08:47.939 --> 01:08:49.202
After dinner?

1061
01:08:49.408 --> 01:08:51.899
Yeah. right after dinner...

1062
01:08:52.110 --> 01:08:55.637
...I felt this little aching.
this burning. you know?

1063
01:08:55.847 --> 01:08:57.145
Low.

1064
01:08:57.350 --> 01:08:58.578
And you have an aneurysm?

1065
01:08:58.784 --> 01:09:02.584
Yeah. they're gonna operate
on me next month.

1066
01:09:03.389 --> 01:09:07.519
Mr. Harvey. we're just waiting
for your old film. so just rest easy.

1067
01:09:07.727 --> 01:09:10.321
We'll fix you up right away.
We'll take care of it.

1068
01:09:10.530 --> 01:09:11.827
Thank you. doctor.

1069
01:09:12.032 --> 01:09:13.760
Okay. thank you.

1070
01:09:14.268 --> 01:09:17.567
He's bleeding into his belly.
He can go anytime. Who's on?

1071
01:09:17.771 --> 01:09:19.601
Ashley and Jimmy
have the appendectomy.

1072
01:09:19.806 --> 01:09:21.864
Gill and Levine are
with the knife wound.

1073
01:09:22.075 --> 01:09:25.135
They pulled Ed to do the lady
with the small bowel.

1074
01:09:25.311 --> 01:09:26.301
Vascular team?

1075
01:09:26.512 --> 01:09:28.776
- In Minneapolis.
- Where's Baker?

1076
01:09:28.982 --> 01:09:30.279
Baker's in the Bahamas.

1077
01:09:30.484 --> 01:09:32.145
This guy could die any minute.

1078
01:09:32.352 --> 01:09:34.343
I know. but there's no one to do him.

1079
01:09:41.061 --> 01:09:44.224
Okay. call Morgenstern.
Tell him to get over here.

1080
01:09:44.431 --> 01:09:46.161
I'm starting a ruptured aneurysm.

1081
01:09:46.367 --> 01:09:48.095
You can't.
You're just a resident.

1082
01:09:48.303 --> 01:09:50.931
What do you want to do?
This guy could die.

1083
01:09:51.239 --> 01:09:52.637
- I know that. but...
- Look!

1084
01:09:52.840 --> 01:09:56.207
I'm just trying to keep him alive
until Morgenstern shows up.

1085
01:09:56.644 --> 01:09:59.943
Now call the O.R. And tell them
to set up for a laparotomy.

1086
01:10:00.148 --> 01:10:01.274
Please.

1087
01:10:06.955 --> 01:10:09.219
This is Dr. Lewis.
Get me Morgenstern.

1088
01:10:09.424 --> 01:10:12.951
Find him! We have an aortic
aneurysm. and Dr. Benton's starting.

1089
01:10:13.162 --> 01:10:15.960
He'd like some help.
That's right. Dr. Benton's starting.

1090
01:10:19.501 --> 01:10:22.095
- What's on?
- Ruptured abdominal aneurysm.

1091
01:10:22.304 --> 01:10:24.534
- Who's doing it?
- Dr. Benton.

1092
01:10:24.740 --> 01:10:26.571
Dr. Benton?

1093
01:10:34.049 --> 01:10:35.710
I'm doing anesthesia for you.

1094
01:10:35.919 --> 01:10:40.014
Great. Get down to the blood bank.
make sure they send us 20 units.

1095
01:10:40.222 --> 01:10:43.351
And get the nurses jumping.
The patient's on his way.

1096
01:10:46.429 --> 01:10:48.727
You sure you're okay about this?

1097
01:10:48.932 --> 01:10:52.026
I'm scared as hell.
The guy's already ruptured his belly.

1098
01:10:52.235 --> 01:10:54.396
He's bleeding to death internally.

1099
01:10:54.604 --> 01:10:57.631
I gotta do him.
I'm his only chance.

1100
01:11:24.035 --> 01:11:26.004
Evening. I wanted you to know...

1101
01:11:26.203 --> 01:11:29.696
...I'll be starting a ruptured
aortic aneurysm in Room 2.

1102
01:11:29.907 --> 01:11:31.967
I'd appreciate a hand
when you have a minute.

1103
01:11:37.416 --> 01:11:40.543
- What did he say?
- He said he's doing an aneurysm.

1104
01:11:40.819 --> 01:11:42.548
That's a joke. isn't it?

1105
01:11:42.754 --> 01:11:45.484
Cheryl? Go make sure he's joking.

1106
01:11:54.166 --> 01:11:56.465
Dr. Ashley. he's doing it.

1107
01:11:56.669 --> 01:11:59.001
You're kidding!
Jim. break and help him.

1108
01:11:59.205 --> 01:12:02.071
I'll finish here
and get there as soon as I can.

1109
01:12:13.587 --> 01:12:16.214
Okay. boys and girls. let's go.
This isn't a picnic.

1110
01:12:16.389 --> 01:12:17.378
Prep. please.

1111
01:12:17.757 --> 01:12:20.352
Prep. please!
Come on. quit staring at me.

1112
01:12:20.561 --> 01:12:22.893
I'm just trying
to keep the poor guy alive.

1113
01:12:23.097 --> 01:12:24.358
All right. plastic.

1114
01:12:25.132 --> 01:12:27.600
- Jimmy's coming in to help.
- Oh. great!

1115
01:12:28.335 --> 01:12:32.328
The only guy that knows less
about vascular surgery than I do.

1116
01:12:32.539 --> 01:12:35.201
- Okay. is Mr. Harvey happy?
- He isn't complaining.

1117
01:12:35.409 --> 01:12:37.570
Then let's do this.
Knife. please.

1118
01:12:38.480 --> 01:12:39.468
Thank you.

1119
01:12:40.080 --> 01:12:42.105
We're starting at 2:13 a.m.

1120
01:12:42.316 --> 01:12:46.980
Let's see how long the chief takes
to get off of his girl and into work.

1121
01:12:49.556 --> 01:12:51.081
Nice and slow.

1122
01:12:51.292 --> 01:12:52.589
Started without you. Jimmy.

1123
01:12:53.495 --> 01:12:54.723
There you go. sir.

1124
01:12:55.195 --> 01:12:57.756
Listen up. We're going
straight down the linea alba.

1125
01:12:57.966 --> 01:13:00.958
Nothing fancy.
The guy's got a 50% mortality anyway.

1126
01:13:01.436 --> 01:13:04.405
Suction.
Thank you. for all the good it'll do.

1127
01:13:04.973 --> 01:13:06.908
Pick up.
Come on. Jimmy. work with me.

1128
01:13:07.108 --> 01:13:08.234
Pick up.

1129
01:13:09.211 --> 01:13:10.768
Lot of blood in there.

1130
01:13:10.979 --> 01:13:12.947
It's precisely his problem.

1131
01:13:13.716 --> 01:13:16.014
Okay. here we go.

1132
01:13:16.218 --> 01:13:18.243
Wish me luck. Knife.

1133
01:13:26.328 --> 01:13:27.818
Systolic's holding at 100.

1134
01:13:31.200 --> 01:13:32.394
Mother!

1135
01:13:33.036 --> 01:13:34.297
Now!

1136
01:13:48.852 --> 01:13:50.342
Can't find it.

1137
01:13:50.854 --> 01:13:51.980
Damn it!

1138
01:13:53.390 --> 01:13:55.517
There! No. no.

1139
01:13:57.160 --> 01:14:00.187
Get your hand in there
and push away the small intestine.

1140
01:14:01.598 --> 01:14:04.465
Where are you. little leak?
How bad is his pressure?

1141
01:14:04.668 --> 01:14:08.161
- You won't like it.
- I won't like it? Think about him.

1142
01:14:08.339 --> 01:14:09.328
Carol...

1143
01:14:09.540 --> 01:14:13.340
...hang 6 more units packed cells
and a unit of plasma and platelets.

1144
01:14:13.543 --> 01:14:14.874
Wait a minute.

1145
01:14:15.912 --> 01:14:17.710
Wait a minute.

1146
01:14:19.784 --> 01:14:21.513
It's too much to hope. huh?

1147
01:14:23.521 --> 01:14:25.285
I got it.

1148
01:14:25.490 --> 01:14:26.889
Yeah. I got it.
Time down.

1149
01:14:27.091 --> 01:14:28.217
Call it out in minutes.

1150
01:14:28.426 --> 01:14:31.691
Let's suck this field clean
so we can see what we're doing.

1151
01:14:31.896 --> 01:14:35.492
Dr. Benton. the chief resident is
in the hospital and on his way.

1152
01:14:35.701 --> 01:14:38.533
Well. suck that field clean.
we got the chief coming!

1153
01:14:38.736 --> 01:14:41.831
We don't want him to think
we don't know what we're doing.

1154
01:14:43.174 --> 01:14:45.939
- Pressure?
- 100 over 70 and falling.

1155
01:14:46.144 --> 01:14:49.375
I won't sweat that.
Let's just keep that blood going in.

1156
01:14:50.616 --> 01:14:52.641
Jimmy. your hands are trembling.

1157
01:14:52.851 --> 01:14:56.150
- I can't imagine why.
- Yeah. well. me neither.

1158
01:14:56.588 --> 01:15:00.650
But everything's cool here.
All we have to do is sit and wait.

1159
01:15:00.860 --> 01:15:03.795
Dr. Ashley will be with you
as soon as he can.

1160
01:15:03.997 --> 01:15:06.988
All of a sudden. I got all
the help I want. huh?

1161
01:15:16.709 --> 01:15:18.734
Start a nitroglycerine drip.

1162
01:15:18.945 --> 01:15:21.573
50 and 250 D5W.
80 of Lasix. IV push.

1163
01:15:21.781 --> 01:15:24.546
Get a CBC. lytes. cardiac enzyme...

1164
01:15:24.751 --> 01:15:27.721
...chest X-ray and a 12-reading EKG.

1165
01:15:28.187 --> 01:15:29.951
You take digitalis. dear?

1166
01:15:30.157 --> 01:15:33.216
Have you taken any today?
This morning?

1167
01:15:33.427 --> 01:15:34.621
Add a dig. Level.

1168
01:15:34.828 --> 01:15:38.559
Meanwhile. 3 milligrams
of morphine. IV push.

1169
01:15:42.937 --> 01:15:44.131
I can't give this up.

1170
01:15:46.073 --> 01:15:48.304
No. no. no.
Not you. you're fine.

1171
01:15:48.709 --> 01:15:52.270
- Your wife on 2204.
- I'll have to call her back.

1172
01:16:14.303 --> 01:16:16.998
Sure taking a long time
getting in here. huh?

1173
01:16:20.609 --> 01:16:23.306
They've been out there scrubbing
for the last month.

1174
01:16:24.914 --> 01:16:29.146
You know. it's times like these
when I get into a reflective mood...

1175
01:16:29.352 --> 01:16:31.286
...and I pause and think of how...

1176
01:16:31.487 --> 01:16:33.717
Good morning. Peter.
Give it to me quick.

1177
01:16:33.923 --> 01:16:37.290
57-year-old male. in good health.
seen here 8 weeks ago...

1178
01:16:37.493 --> 01:16:40.429
...where he was found to have
a pulsatile abdominal mass...

1179
01:16:40.630 --> 01:16:42.656
...with aortic calcification on X-ray.

1180
01:16:42.999 --> 01:16:44.934
Surgery was scheduled for next month.

1181
01:16:45.135 --> 01:16:48.400
But this evening. he had
intermittent pain in the mid-back.

1182
01:16:48.605 --> 01:16:50.071
When he got here. he had...

1183
01:16:50.272 --> 01:16:53.639
...a distended abdomen. peritoneal
irritation and reduced hematocrit.

1184
01:16:53.843 --> 01:16:56.141
So you decided to open him up.

1185
01:16:56.346 --> 01:16:58.644
This is the worst incision
I've seen in a while.

1186
01:16:59.216 --> 01:17:02.413
A good veterinarian would do
a better skin cut than that.

1187
01:17:03.153 --> 01:17:05.451
All right. hold on.

1188
01:17:08.826 --> 01:17:09.884
Got it.

1189
01:17:10.061 --> 01:17:11.050
What's his pressure?

1190
01:17:11.262 --> 01:17:14.322
90 over 65.
and he's gotten 12 units.

1191
01:17:14.532 --> 01:17:17.432
We'll take over from here.
try to make something out of it.

1192
01:17:17.634 --> 01:17:20.229
Hey. humor me.
Have some dopamine standing by.

1193
01:17:20.438 --> 01:17:22.234
Hoover that. will you?

1194
01:17:24.676 --> 01:17:26.507
Sounds like a plan.
Good.

1195
01:17:26.711 --> 01:17:28.906
Give me a little more room in there.

1196
01:17:29.114 --> 01:17:30.274
Thank you.

1197
01:17:32.216 --> 01:17:33.741
Look at that.

1198
01:17:39.257 --> 01:17:41.088
You did a good job.

1199
01:17:41.560 --> 01:17:44.028
You were lucky.
but you were right to open him up.

1200
01:17:44.595 --> 01:17:45.857
Good work.

1201
01:17:46.298 --> 01:17:47.697
Yeah. clear it out.

1202
01:17:48.199 --> 01:17:49.292
Let me see if I can...

1203
01:17:49.768 --> 01:17:51.565
Pull it out for a second.

1204
01:17:52.805 --> 01:17:55.774
That's what we want. right there.
That's right.

1205
01:18:22.035 --> 01:18:25.334
Why is he still crying?
Why haven't you given him something?

1206
01:18:29.075 --> 01:18:33.137
Look! He's still crying.
Why aren't you giving him something?

1207
01:18:33.346 --> 01:18:36.441
I can't until I know
the extent of his injuries.

1208
01:18:36.650 --> 01:18:38.914
He's been to X-ray.
We saw a skull fracture.

1209
01:18:39.119 --> 01:18:41.610
A skull fracture?
The babysitter!

1210
01:18:41.989 --> 01:18:43.183
I never trusted her.

1211
01:18:43.390 --> 01:18:46.188
Your child has contusions
that are 12 hours old.

1212
01:18:46.393 --> 01:18:50.762
He has a skull fracture. He also has
several old healed fractures.

1213
01:18:50.966 --> 01:18:52.956
This is a battered child.

1214
01:18:54.869 --> 01:18:59.034
I'm not even gonna respond to that.
You think I'd harm my child?

1215
01:18:59.241 --> 01:19:00.435
It happens all the time.

1216
01:19:00.641 --> 01:19:02.337
I'm taking him home.

1217
01:19:02.544 --> 01:19:05.376
- No! You have anything to say?
- He's my date.

1218
01:19:11.052 --> 01:19:12.815
Look.

1219
01:19:13.021 --> 01:19:15.182
I can assure you. whoever you are...

1220
01:19:15.690 --> 01:19:17.123
Dr. Ross.

1221
01:19:18.994 --> 01:19:23.021
Dr. Ross. let me tell you
your concerns are unfounded. okay?

1222
01:19:25.467 --> 01:19:27.402
How'd he burn his legs?

1223
01:19:27.603 --> 01:19:29.537
These marks right here.
On his legs.

1224
01:19:30.305 --> 01:19:34.242
Those are healed burn scars.
How did that happen?

1225
01:19:39.515 --> 01:19:44.317
I don't know anything about burns.
I think you're making this up.

1226
01:19:44.520 --> 01:19:46.750
- You might call an attorney.
- I am an attorney!

1227
01:19:46.956 --> 01:19:49.322
Then you know what Child Services
will do.

1228
01:19:49.525 --> 01:19:50.890
How dare you?

1229
01:19:51.094 --> 01:19:54.962
How dare you treat your child
like this? He's a little kid!

1230
01:19:55.732 --> 01:20:00.169
I try to be understanding in my job.
But. lady. this just stinks.

1231
01:20:13.383 --> 01:20:15.544
- You find that chart?
- I can't find it.

1232
01:20:15.752 --> 01:20:17.084
- Well. find it!
- I don't...

1233
01:20:17.288 --> 01:20:19.620
Do you think I am deaf?
I heard you.

1234
01:20:19.824 --> 01:20:23.623
- Now find me the chart!
- I told you. I don't know where it is!

1235
01:20:32.737 --> 01:20:33.863
Is it okay?

1236
01:20:34.072 --> 01:20:36.165
You can go now.
You did the right thing.

1237
01:20:36.374 --> 01:20:38.673
I mean. is the baby okay?

1238
01:20:40.545 --> 01:20:41.807
He will be.

1239
01:20:52.223 --> 01:20:53.486
Oh. man!

1240
01:20:55.627 --> 01:20:57.493
So how's Hathaway?

1241
01:20:58.230 --> 01:20:59.754
It doesn't look good.

1242
01:21:01.200 --> 01:21:03.168
They contact her family?

1243
01:21:03.602 --> 01:21:05.035
Yeah. they found them.

1244
01:21:07.473 --> 01:21:09.941
So how'd your aortic aneurysm go?

1245
01:21:10.242 --> 01:21:12.006
Morgenstern showed.

1246
01:21:13.479 --> 01:21:16.415
<i>Dr. Benton to Trauma 1.
Dr. Benton to Trauma 1.</i>

1247
01:21:19.853 --> 01:21:21.787
No rest for the wicked.

1248
01:21:25.592 --> 01:21:27.924
Jerry. Perez. Let's go.

1249
01:21:28.128 --> 01:21:30.927
- What's the problem?
- We picked him up in Old Town.

1250
01:21:31.131 --> 01:21:34.066
He was standing. blocking traffic.

1251
01:21:34.267 --> 01:21:36.964
But he's got that smell.
so I thought I'd check.

1252
01:21:37.637 --> 01:21:39.434
You did the right thing.

1253
01:21:39.639 --> 01:21:42.837
We got a diabetic ketoacidosis.
Let's go.

1254
01:21:43.109 --> 01:21:44.805
You probably saved his life.

1255
01:21:48.849 --> 01:21:50.441
What do you want. a medal?

1256
01:21:52.720 --> 01:21:55.120
Give him 10 units regular insulin.
IV push.

1257
01:21:55.323 --> 01:21:57.121
Start a drip. 10 units per hour.

1258
01:21:57.325 --> 01:22:00.727
I want him hydrated as soon
as possible with normal saline.

1259
01:22:00.928 --> 01:22:02.225
And you want KCI?

1260
01:22:02.430 --> 01:22:04.830
Not on your life.
Get a CBC and lytes.

1261
01:22:05.033 --> 01:22:07.933
Call me with the potassium.
and get a blood gas.

1262
01:22:08.904 --> 01:22:11.338
Did you get the message
your wife called?

1263
01:22:11.539 --> 01:22:12.631
No.

1264
01:22:16.144 --> 01:22:18.009
I'll call her in the morning.

1265
01:22:20.449 --> 01:22:22.212
Hello. Mrs. Harvey.

1266
01:22:22.551 --> 01:22:25.042
Okay. let's have a look here.

1267
01:22:33.061 --> 01:22:34.689
He seems to be doing fine.

1268
01:22:34.897 --> 01:22:36.659
Oh. I'm so grateful.

1269
01:22:36.866 --> 01:22:40.495
Dr. Morgenstern came so quickly.
He saved his life.

1270
01:22:41.571 --> 01:22:44.699
Yes. well. Dr. Morgenstern's
a wonderful surgeon.

1271
01:22:44.907 --> 01:22:46.397
He said you did a lot too.

1272
01:22:49.412 --> 01:22:52.871
Actually. I just helped out
a little bit. That's all.

1273
01:22:53.349 --> 01:22:55.442
I'll check on you later. okay?

1274
01:23:16.673 --> 01:23:18.869
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

1275
01:23:26.450 --> 01:23:28.442
You want some coffee?

1276
01:23:30.755 --> 01:23:31.847
Sure.

1277
01:23:40.698 --> 01:23:44.225
I wouldn't kid you about that.
I had a few.

1278
01:23:44.803 --> 01:23:46.703
Maybe more than a few.

1279
01:23:47.972 --> 01:23:50.304
Hell of a party. though!

1280
01:23:53.312 --> 01:23:55.803
Okay. Mr. Murphy. you are done.

1281
01:23:56.014 --> 01:23:57.346
Already?

1282
01:23:59.551 --> 01:24:01.019
I didn't feel a thing.

1283
01:24:01.220 --> 01:24:02.881
No. I didn't.

1284
01:24:03.656 --> 01:24:04.953
I still don't.

1285
01:24:05.691 --> 01:24:10.321
<i>And he was in. I guess. ten days.
And you know what it cost?</i>

1286
01:24:10.529 --> 01:24:13.431
<i>$ 24.000.
More than $ 24.000!</i>

1287
01:24:13.632 --> 01:24:15.293
<i>That's what it cost.</i>

1288
01:24:15.735 --> 01:24:20.570
<i>And I want to know where doctors
get off charging money like that?</i>

1289
01:24:20.773 --> 01:24:23.367
<i>Medical costs certainly
are on the rise.</i>

1290
01:24:23.577 --> 01:24:26.239
<i>That's why we need
national health insurance.</i>

1291
01:24:26.446 --> 01:24:30.211
<i>It's a scandal! Those doctors
should be ashamed of themselves.</i>

1292
01:24:30.884 --> 01:24:34.615
<i>Many of them are. I'm sure.
Let's hear what folks out there think.</i>

1293
01:24:34.822 --> 01:24:38.882
<i>Call Carl Barker on Nightline.
We'll be back in just a minute.</i>

1294
01:24:41.963 --> 01:24:43.897
That's it? Anybody else?

1295
01:24:44.132 --> 01:24:47.100
Well. I got a little problem.
My throat's acting up.

1296
01:24:47.435 --> 01:24:49.265
You need to see a doctor.

1297
01:24:49.469 --> 01:24:52.132
- Which room?
- Five and six are open.

1298
01:24:52.340 --> 01:24:53.432
Five.

1299
01:25:12.461 --> 01:25:13.792
Is that it?

1300
01:25:13.996 --> 01:25:16.362
Well. my throat.
I've got some soreness.

1301
01:25:16.564 --> 01:25:17.964
I'll be in Room 8.

1302
01:25:18.167 --> 01:25:20.431
You got a pen?
Wake me at 6:30.

1303
01:25:20.636 --> 01:25:23.196
That gives you an hour and a half.
You're lucky.

1304
01:25:50.266 --> 01:25:52.427
6:30. Dr. Greene.
